title: christmas fruitcake
directions: In a large bowl, combine all candied fruit and raisins.
Pour sherry over fruit.
Soak overnight.
Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs until very light.
Add flour (reserve a little to flour fruit).

title: banana butterscotch pudding
directions: Combine the brown sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan and cook until sugar is melted and mixture bubbles up.
Serve hot or cold over sliced bananas.
For a more elaborate dessert, this may be served with whipped cream or whipped evaporated milk.
Makes 5 servings.

title: possum pie
directions: Grease pie plate.
To egg whites, add sugar, vanilla, Ritz crackers and nuts.
Pour in pie plate and bake 25 minutes at 325°. Cool crust.
Whip the cream; add powdered sugar.
Cover baked pie and top with coconut.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: dumplings for fruit
directions: Lightly grease pan with oleo.
Place fruit and juice in pan on stove.
Heat until warm.
Drop dough by tablespoon.
Cook 20 minutes, slow.
Good with Cool Whip or ice cream topping or plain. May also be microwaved.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: In shallow, greased baking dish, mix soup, water, mushrooms, rice, paprika and half of the pepper. Place chicken over rice mixture and sprinkle with remaining pepper. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake for an additional 15 minutes to brown chicken.

title: applesauce-pecan bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in pecans and raisins.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg, applesauce and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon mixture into a greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/4 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Let cool on wire rack.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Pour this mixture over chicken and vegetables.
Bake at 425° until brown (about 30 minutes).

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: Place chicken and celery in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and curry powder.
Add chicken mixture and mix well.
Cover and chill for at least 30 minutes.
Before serving, add pineapple, oranges and coconut; toss gently.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Serve on salad greens if desired.

title: ham-it-up skillet
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Saute ham in oil.
Gradually stir in liquid.
Add (uncooked) rice.
Cover.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in parsley and olives.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all well together.
Chill before serving.

title: tuna-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Place soup in a saucepan; add milk and mayonnaise, gradually.
Heat until smooth.
Combine macaroni, tuna, onion, pimento, peas, salt, pepper and mushroom mixture. Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and sprinkle with grated cheese and potato chips on top.
Bake in a 350° oven until heated through and cheese is melted, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: aunt jean's shrimp casserole
directions: Cook shrimp in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, salad oil and melted butter.
Cook rice and drain; refrigerate all.

title: dewberry dream delight
directions: Mix and
press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool while doing filling.

title: glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a small bowl; stir until smooth and drizzle over warm cake.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes, cheese and other ingredients.
Rub lump of butter on top.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fruit rollspringfield, missouri
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk, butter, baking powder, vanilla and salt and put batter in a 9 X 13-inch greased and floured jelly roll pan.

title: quick boston baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients (except bacon) together.
Put in a baking dish and add bacon slices on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer in following order in baking dish:
stuffing, chicken and broccoli.
In medium saucepan, combine the broth, margarine, flour, milk, sherry and egg.
Cook all until thickened; pour over layers in the baking dish.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tuna mix casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add tuna and mushroom or chicken soup and milk mixture.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Cook at 425° for 10 minutes.
Or microwave it 3 to 5 minutes, just until cheese is melted.
Stir.
Use microwave dish.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter or bacon grease in large skillet until transparent. Add okra slices and saute 5 minutes longer. Add remaining ingredients and simmer covered for 20 minutes. Yield 6 servings.

title: strawberry pecan torte
directions: You will need a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush cookies in food processor.
Combine cookies, soft ice cream and Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cheese needs to be at room temperature.
Mix together and form into 2 balls.
Cool.
Roll in chopped nuts on foil.

title: moravian sugar cake
directions: Using a large bowl, add shortening and sugar to hot mashed potatoes.
Add beaten eggs.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm potato water and add sifted flour and salt.
Let rise in covered bowl until double in bulk.
Pat out in greased pans to 1/2 inch thickness.
Let rise 1 hour.
Use four pans 11 x 7 x 2 inches. Indent and fill holes with plenty of butter.
Sprinkle generously with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crumble cookies in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Reserve 1/2 cup to sprinkle on top.
Pour margarine over cookies.

title: scrapple
directions: Bring 2 cups of water to boil.
Mix cold water, cornmeal and salt together.
Add slowly to boiling water.
Bring to boil; cover immediately.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, crumble and fry sausage; drain off fat.
Add cooked sausage to cornmeal mixture. Put in loaf pan and refrigerate for several hours.
When ready to use, slice, roll in flour and cook in oil until golden brown. Serve immediately with butter and syrup or jelly.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix bananas, sugar, shortening and eggs well, then add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a loaf pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt together chocolate bark and peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies, peanuts and marshmallows.
Stir all together and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: the great depression cake
directions: In large saucepan, simmer sugar, coffee, shortening, raisins and apples for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cool 10 minutes. Blend the remaining ingredients and stir into mixture.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.
Water can be substituted for coffee.
Candied fruit may be added for an easy fruitcake.
Recipe dates back to 1929.

title: chicken divan
directions: Grease or spray casserole.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli, drain and arrange in
1 1/2-quart greased casserole. Simmer
chicken in small amount of	water
minutes.
Drain chicken and arrange on broccoli.
Mix
next
4 ingredients and pour over top.
Sprinkle cheese.
Mix bread crumbs with butter and top.
Bake 25 minutes and serve over rice.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Add sugar.
Grate lemon rind into this.
Add lemons (juice and rind) and oleo to eggs and sugar.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Beat egg whites stiff for meringue.
Bake at 325° until almost set.
Spread meringue on top of pie and brown.

title: lemon glaze
directions: Mix ingredients together until desired consistency.
Lemon juice should be added to your personal taste.

title: brazil nut pie
directions: Combine
eggs,	sour
cream,
sugar,
flour and vanilla. Beat at medium speed with electric mixer.
Stir in raisins and nuts. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes then reduce to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef with diced onion and garlic salt.
Drain and cool completely.
Mix with the remaining ingredients and serve.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, add ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and add 2 1/4 cups flour and mix again.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in 400° oven for approximately 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen medium sized cookies.
Moist and yummy.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients in the blender.

title: pizza ole
directions: Brown the meat; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, water and seasoning mix.
Simmer 5 minutes,
stirring occasionally.
Add beans;
mix lightly.
Press dough onto bottom
and
sides
of greased 12-inch pizza pan;
prick with fork. Bake
at 425° for 7 to 8 minutes until browned.
Cover with
meat
mixture
and cheese cubes.
Continue baking until cheese
is
melted.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with
guacamole if desired. Serves 4.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until tender; drain well. Place in 11 x 14-inch baking dish. Blend flour and margarine in saucepan. Add milk and cheese. Cook over medium heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly. Pour over potatoes. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pizza bread
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough.
Spread in slightly oiled pan.
Layer salami, pepperoni and cheeses.
Overlap edges to form a log, sealed at the edges.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and brown sugar thoroughly. Gradually add sugar.
Continue creaming.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Sift baking powder with flour; add alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour. Add vanilla and blend well.
Turn batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 90 minutes or until cake test done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, put into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle on French fried onions and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: golden chiffon cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients into bowl and make a well in center and add in order listed, the oil, egg yolks, cold water, vanilla and lemon rind.
Beat all together at medium speed for 1 minute. Measure into large mixing bowl, egg whites, making about 1 cup and add cream of tartar.
Beat until egg whites form very stiff peaks on high speed for 3 to 5 minutes.
Do not underbeat.
Egg whites are stiff when a dry spatula drawn through leaves a clean path. Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over beaten whites, gently folding with whisk just until blended.
Do not stir.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 55 minutes and then at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes longer.
You may need to put foil over top for the last 10 minutes or so.
Hang over a coke bottle to cool. Delicious.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil sugar, water, syrup and salt to soft ball stage (238°). Add vanilla, vinegar and butter.
Cook to hard ball stage (266°). Pour over popped corn and peanuts.
Mix together.

title: banana-blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese. Spread on the pie crust. Slice bananas. Top with Cool Whip. Put the blueberry pie filling on top.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a heavy 3-quart saucepan. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks slightly, using a fork.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Immediately pour yolk mixture back into hot mixture, blending thoroughly.
Cook two more minutes over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Gently stir in vanilla and butter.
Cool completely.
Fold whipped cream into cooled filling.
Then fold in 1 cup of the coconut. Pour mixture into baked pie shell.
Chill in refrigerator until set, about 2 hours.
Sprinkle top of pie with the remaining 1/3 cup of coconut before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
The whipped cream folded into the coconut custard filling makes it light and delicate.

title: curried chicken puffs
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Add flour and salt; stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms ball.
Remove from heat; add eggs, one at a time, heating until smooth after each addition.
Place level measuring tablespoonfuls of batter on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Cool.

title: strawberry pretzel surprise
directions: Note:
Sugar-free jello, fat-free pretzels, light oleo, light cream cheese and lite Cool Whip may be used to reduce calories.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and salt; add melted butter and stir well.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix well and add buttermilk, vanilla and coconut. Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bakeless cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add the remaining ingredients. Crumble 3/4 pound vanilla wafers; use alternate layers of the crumbs and the batter and pour in and fill greased pan.
Store in refrigerator for at least 1 hour or overnight.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: cabbage goulash
directions: Brown meat and onion; salt to taste.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients except for cabbage.
Mix well.
Stir in cabbage and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until cabbage is tender.
Even people who don't like cabbage love this dish.

title: pork steak and potatoes
directions: Season pork steak with desired seasonings.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with potatoes.
Add soup and spread over potatoes. Add water and bake uncovered for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cocktail hour dates
directions: Fill pitted dates with cheese spread, then top with a cashew. Display on a bed of parsley.

title: quick white bean soup
directions: Cook onions and carrots in butter until onion is transparent. Add beans and 1 can of water and can of ham.
Mash beans with potato masher or fork slightly.
Cook on low for about 5 minutes. Great with cornbread.

title: marybeth's poundcake
directions: Put margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla in bowl and beat 1/2 minute at low speed.
Beat 5 minutes at high speed.
On low speed, mix in flour mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour).

title: edible play dough
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
If sticky, add little more powdered milk.
Decorate, if desired, with raisins or coconut or use your imagination.
For children, 18 months to adults.

title: lo-cal fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple (keep juice).
Mix all fruit.
Mix pineapple juice and pudding.
Pour over fruit.

title: stuffed (cubed) strip steak
directions: Pan-fry strip steaks.
Prepare stuffing.
Put layer of stuffing on cooked steaks.
Simmer about 10 minutes; add beef gravy.
When ready, put 1 slice cheese on top.
Simmer until cheese is softened, then serve.

title: mashed potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, margarine, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add milk and vanilla; mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Boil sugar, syrup and water. Pour slowly into egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Roll out on powdered sugar.
Spread peanut butter and roll up into jelly roll. Let cool and cut as you would a jelly roll.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: texas hamburgers
directions: In a medium-sized skillet, melt 1/4 cup margarine.
Add chopped onion and saute until transparent (about 3 minutes).
Stir in brown sugar, catsup, water, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Spread buns with margarine.
Place hamburgers and sauce in buns.

title: sweet noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
In blender, mix milk, sugar, butter and eggs.
Pour over noodles.
Place in greased baking dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours. Raisins may be added to recipe, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine in large mixing bowl and mix well. Pour in 9 x 13 (sprayed with Pam) pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese. Dilute soup with water and pour over chicken and cheese.
Toss stuffing mix and oleo until stuffing has been coated.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: three-cheese stuffed southwestern chiles
directions: Choose Poblano chilies that are small (larger versions are usually a lot hotter).
Choose Anaheim chilies that are fat (they usually aren't as hot as Poblanos).
Pierce chilies at least twice with a fork.
Char chilies over open flames (barbecue) or under oven broiler, turning when needed, until skin bubbles and darkens. Remove chilies and place in plastic bag.
Seal bag and let chilies steam until cool.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix onion soup mix, rice, mushrooms and water chestnuts in bottom of casserole; pour at least half of the canned soups and water into the other mixture and mix well.
Salt chicken pieces and place on top of other mixture.
Pour remaining soups and water over entire mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours, or until chicken is tender.
Raise chicken pieces now and then and stir rice mixture to make sure it is loose and moist.
Uncover near end of cooking time.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in luke warm water.
Combine cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and yeast mixture.
Add flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Let rise 50 to 60 minutes, then stir dough down.
Turn into a well-greased baking dish.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Brush with butter; sprinkle with salt.

title: bisquick mix
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients until it resembles cornmeal.
Store in covered container.

title: broccoli-and-squash casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli in a large steamer basket over boiling water.
Cover and steam 5 to 8 minutes or until crisp-tender; remove from basket.
Add squash and onion to basket and repeat procedure.
Combine squash, onion and butter in a large bowl; mash.
Stir in broccoli, eggs and next 3 ingredients; spoon into two, lightly greased, 2-quart baking dishes.
Sprinkle evenly with breadcrumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden. Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: shaped sugar cookies
directions: Mix and set aside sour cream and baking soda.
Combine sugar, shortening, eggs, salt, vanilla and baking powder.
Add sour cream and flour.
Mix all together.
Roll out.
Cut and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: breakfast cups
directions: Combine rice, 1/2 cup cheese, sausage, chilies, milk, eggs, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Evenly divide mixture into 12 muffin cups, coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle rest of cheese over filled cups and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
May be frozen and reheated in the microwave.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon, drain and crumble.
Add to broccoli, raisins and onion.
Mix together Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over the broccoli mixture.
Set in fridge for 2 hours to cool and blend flavors.

title: homemade bread
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 400°.
Bake in bread pan 55 to 60 minutes.
Add spices, dried fruits, nuts, etc. for variety.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Cut or tear washed spinach into small pieces.
Slice chestnuts paper thin.
Drain bean sprouts.
Combine spinach, water chestnuts, bean sprouts, eggs and bacon.
Toss.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork roast
directions: Make slits in the roast. Place some fruit in each slit. In a bowl, combine the water, honey, soup mix, ketchup and lemon juice. Mix well. Place roast fat side up in a roasting pan. Pour mixture over top. Cover and bake at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: coconut snowballs
directions: Scoop ice cream into balls.
Roll in coconut.
(Can roll in optional ingredients.)
Serve immediately or place in shallow pan. Cover and store in freezer.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add enchilada sauce.
Mix in soup, water and chiles and heat.
In 2-quart dish layer tortillas (torn into pieces), meat mixture and soup mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight or all day.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Melt chocolate.
(I melt it in microwave and watch very closely.)
Pour over mixture and stir to coat.
Spread mixture on waxed paper.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Then shape into a loaf. Cook for 30 minutes.
Then mix last 3 ingredients together and spread it over meat loaf and cook for 15 more minutes.
When cooking, cook it at 350°.

title: krispy kritters
directions: Heat sugar and syrup together until sugar is dissolved, do not boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter; mix well.
Add cereal and stir until coated.
Pat into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together.
Spread evenly over cereal mixture.
Let set, then cut into squares.

title: bran muffins
directions: Add bran to molasses and milk. Allow to soak 15 minutes.
Beat egg and add to mixture.

title: cheese roll
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Divide in 3 equal parts and form into rolls.
Sprinkle paprika on wax paper and roll each roll in paprika. Chill, then slice.

title: buttermilk baked chicken
directions: Melt butter in pan. Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Roll in flour mixture and put in pan, skin side down.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 30 minutes. Turn and bake for 15 minutes.
Mix soup and 1 cup buttermilk; pour mixture around chicken.
Stir gravy.
Cook until heated through and serve with chicken.
Yields 4 servings.

title: jailhouse rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast
in
warm
water and set aside.
Combine potatoes, eggs, salt, sugar and margarine.
Blend in flour and add yeast.
Put in a greased bowl and cover with a damp cloth. Put in refrigerator
until
ready
to
use.
Pinch off enough dough to make
a dozen or so rolls.
Put the remainder back in the refrigerator and cover with damp cloth.
Roll the dough to the desired
thickness
and
cut out with biscuit cutter.
Let rise, then bake at 375° until done.
You may cut out all rolls and use what you want then freeze the rest.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix soup, vinegar, sugar and mustard. Pour over carrots and onions; chill 24 hours before serving.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix and knead dough until soft, not sticky.
Pat or roll into 1/4-inch circles.
Make small hole in center.
Fry in deep fat (350°).

title: cookies and cream pie
directions: Pour milk into large mixing bowl.
Add instant pudding.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute or until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping and chopped cookies.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes before cutting.
Yields 8 servings. Store leftover in freezer.

title: fried pies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and shortening until fine.
Mix eggs with cream; combine with flour mixture.
Beat until stretchy. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out circles, using a small saucer as guide.
Fill with fruit which has been cooked, sweetened, thickened and set overnight.
Wet over filling; press with fork tines around edges.
Fry in deep oil until golden brown.

title: fudge topping for ice cream
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in double boiler.
Gradually add sugar and salt; blend.
Gradually add evaporated milk; cook until thick, about 10 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Once cool, store in refrigerator.

title: mint brownies
directions: Add cocoa to melted margarine.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: cajun sausage and rice
directions: Bring 3 1/2 c. water to a boil in large saucepan. Add rice mix, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Heat 1 tsp. oil in large skillet. Add peppers and saute about 5 minutes. Add sausage and cook for about 3 minutes or until lightly browned. Place meat mixture on top of rice but don't stir. Cover and simmer for about 10 minutes until rice is tender. Stir to mix and serve.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar real well, then add 1 egg at a time, unbeaten.
Take pecans and 1 cup of flour to flour fruit; pour batter over fruit and mix.
Cook in pressure cooker for 1 hour at 10 pounds of pressure.
Take out of cooker and cook in oven for 30 minutes at 250°.
Can be baked in oven at 250° until done, 3 to 4 hours, without pressure.

title: corn and sausage bake
directions: Combine creamed corn, green pepper and onion.
Place half the mixture in bottom of a 10 x 6 x 2-inch buttered baking dish. Sprinkle 3/4 cup coarsely broken crackers over corn.
Add remaining corn.
Top with 3/4 cup crackers.
Mix milk, salt and black pepper.
Pour over corn mixture. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes. Brown sausage links. Serve on top of baked corn.

title: andrea's blueberry pie
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Stir in blueberries and place in a prepared pie crust.
Spread 2 tablespoons butter over this and top with crust (lattice or crumb).
Bake at 450° for first 20 minutes, then reduce to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Then add 5 cups flour.
Mix well until gravy like mixture.
Then add 4 to 5 cups flour.
Knead for about four minutes.
Let rise about one hour and then shape.

title: cocoa cake
directions: Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) round baking pans.
In large bowl, beat together butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat until well combined.
On piece of waxed paper, sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add to butter mixture alternately with milk, beating just until well combined.
Divide batter into prepared pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until center springs back when touched.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pans.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all 5 ingredients well. Then form into a ball. You can chop some nuts and roll the ball in the nuts. Keep in the fridge.

title: broken glass salad
directions: Dissolve each package of jello separately in flat pans using 1 1/2 cups hot water for each.
Chill and cut into cubes when set.

title: convenient refrigerator cole slaw
directions: *Dilute 1/4 cup if too sour.

title: cold cut ribbons
directions: Prepare spread by combining cream cheese, onion and mustard. Lightly spread cream cheese on slice of meat.
Top with cheese slice, more cream cheese and another slice of meat.
Repeat process until stack includes 3 layers of meat and cheese, with cream cheese in between.
Freeze cold cut stack uncut for approximately 1 hour.
When firm, cut into 1 x 2-inch ribbon strips.
Center a pickle slice on each cold cut ribbon.
Skewer with cellophane tipped toothpick and serve.
Makes 30 ribbons.

title: stuffing
directions: Break bread into small pieces into a large bowl. Melt butter in a small pan. Add water very slowly.
Pour over bread. Add salt, pepper and sage.
Mix together.
Make into large balls or use to stuff chicken.

title: mom's cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour or cornstarch.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add milk gradually.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Spread on pie; brown in oven.

title: mrs. gelber's panama torte
directions: Cream sugar with eggs until white.
Add nuts and coffee. Finally, add the baking powder.
Bake in a moderately warm oven in 2 layers.

title: punch
directions: Mix citric acid, boiling water and sugar the night before in order to chill.
It will be syrupy.
Mix orange and pineapple juices with citric acid mixture and 2 gallons of water.

title: ring tum tiddy
directions: Put tomatoes in saucepan.
Add pinch of salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add egg, stirring into the cheese and tomatoes until hot.
Serve on toast for 4 to 8 people depending on appetites.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper and add other ingredients. Put in casserole dish; add cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 350° until it bubbles.
Serves 12.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter or margarine until mushrooms exude liquid.
Then stir in flour.
Cook until flour is slightly browned, stirring frequently.
The mixture will be very, very dry.
Add stock slowly, stirring constantly, and cook until thickened.
Add chicken, seasonings and peas.
Lower heat and continue cooking while you beat egg yolk and milk together.
Stir this into chicken.
Continue stirring until blended.
Serve on toast, rice or in baked patty shells.
Serves 4.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Roll into balls and smash with a glass bottom dipped into sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: barbeque sauce
directions: Mix all together and beat.
Use as desired on spareribs, chicken, beef or chicken.

title: hamburger macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Combine soups, pepper, macaroni, and hamburger.
Place half in a greased 2 qt. casserole.
Sprinkle with half the cheese and onions.
Top with another layer of macaroni mixture and cheese.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease 6 (6 ounce) custard cups.
Beat eggs slightly.
Beat into flour, milk and salt until just smooth. Fill cups 1/2 full.
Bake 20 minutes and reduce heat.
Bake 20 minutes longer for custard cups.

title: my original chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts with celery and onion until tender; remove bone and skin.
Cut into cubes.
Add grapes, nuts, salt and pepper.
Mix dressing and mayonnaise and add to chicken.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine buttermilk, sugar, melted shortening and salt.
Stir flour and soda into a large bowl.
Mix yeast mixture with buttermilk and add to flour; mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes. Form into rolls or cut into desired shapes.
Melt some butter in bottom of baking pan; place rolls in butter and turn over to apply butter on both sides.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook
macaroni	according to package directions; drain. For cheese
sauce:
In	a
saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour, salt
and
pepper.	Add
milk
at once;
cook and stir until thick
and	bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 or 2 minutes more. Add 1 1/2 cups cheese and stir mixture until cheese is melted.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough warm water to make stiff dough.
Roll dough into balls about the size of a large lemon.
Roll balls with rolling pin to about 6 to 8 inches in diameter.
Bake on ungreased cast-iron skillet until done. Tortillas will be white when done with light brown spots.
Do not bake until brown all over.
Serve hot.

title: asparagus vinaigrette
directions: Cook asparagus according to package directions or fresh asparagus
until
tender.
Drain and cool.	Clean tomatoes and cut in half.
Heat dressing to boiling; add tomatoes and heat through.
Pour
over
cooled
asparagus
when
ready to serve. Serves 8.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Put 2 tablespoons oil in a frying pan big enough for the roast. Coat the roast with 2 tablespoons of flour.
Brown on all sides (brown well).
Take the roast up and put into a Dutch oven.
Add the cream of mushroom soup, dry onion soup mix and three cups of water into the pan that you browned the roast in.
Heat and then pour over roast.
Cover with lid or foil.
Simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender, turning occasionally.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 40 minutes longer.

title: precious pink punch
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Just before serving combine ingredients and pour over crushed ice.
Garnish with lemon slices and mint.
Makes 14 scrumptious 8 ounce servings.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Blend all together slowly and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 35 minutes in tube pan.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: You can use vegetables of preference.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain all vegetables.
Add Velveeta cheese, cut up; add the oleo.
Mix well and put into a flat casserole dish.
Cover with 1 tube crushed crackers mixed with 1/2 stick melted oleo. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: heavenly jello salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese.
Add Cool Whip and drained fruit.
Cool.

title: pineapple delight pie
directions: In a big pan mix all ingredients together and cook until thickened.
Let cool, then spread in pie crust and add Cool Whip on top (or as you cut it).
This is enough pie filling to fill 2 medium pie shells.
Regular shells or graham cracker shells can be used!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt, vanilla and soda.
Add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add beaten egg and mix thoroughly.
Mix flour with baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk, mixing well.
Drop from tip of teaspoon on baking sheet, greased with shortening.
Let stand a few minutes.
Then flatten cookies by stamping with a glass covered with a damp cloth.
Bake in moderately hot 375° oven.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Grease baking pan.
Let Karo syrup and sugar come to a boil. Remove and add peanut butter.
Stir well and add to Rice Krispies. Stir well and put in baking pan.
Cut into squares when really cooled.
Melt butterscotch or chocolate morsels in dish over hot water.
Stir and spread over top of squares before cooling.

title: 5 can soup
directions: Saute ground meat, onion and celery together and add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and simmer.

title: no crust cheesecake
directions: Beat ingredients in mixing bowl and pour into ungreased pie pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Bake until top is lightly browned.
Remove and cool 20 minutes.

title: pecan sandies cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Flatten and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Combine pineapple, cheese and flour, mixing until well blended.
(Sometimes I have to use a little of the pineapple juice to blend the ingredients.)
Pour into baking dish and put crushed Ritz crackers on top of mixture.
Pour melted margarine on top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is delicious as a side dish with meats.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a large see-through glass bowl, place 1 layer of each in this order: lettuce, onion, frozen peas and eggs.

title: rachel pafford's baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken breasts; salt and pepper to taste and wrap 1 strip of bacon around each piece of chicken. Lay chicken in baking dish.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice onions, potatoes and celery.
Combine the potatoes, celery, onions and bouillon cubes in a 4-quart pan and cover with water.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
When tender, add half and half, salt and pepper.
Do not let soup boil after adding half and half.
Reduce heat to low.
Finally, enjoy!

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients. Add eggs, water and vanilla. Mix well. In another bowl, mix flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Add flour mixture to first bowl of ingredients. Add oatmeal and chocolate chips. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix together in saucepan until warm.
Serve with chips.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Oven Method:
Mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with potato chips or corn flakes.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour over chicken. Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: blueberry flummery
directions: Place about 1/3 of the fruit at a time in an electric blender. Blend until smooth.
Combine fruit, lemon juice, water, sugar and tapioca in a saucepan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cinnamon.
Serve warm or chilled with whipped cream.

title: trimmed-down cheese grits
directions: Bring water to a boil in medium saucepan. Add grits.

Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Add salt and next 3 ingredients, stirring until cheese melts. Stir a small amount of hot grits into egg substitute; add to remaining grits, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture into a 1-quart baking dish coated with vegetable spray. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until mixture is set.

title: barbecue pot roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides in oil in large Dutch oven.
Combine tomato sauce, water, onions, garlic, salt and pepper, mixing well. Pour over roast.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over roast.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender.

title: quick one egg cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat an 8-inch round cake pan with cooking spray or shortening.
Sift any dry ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Add oil.
Add egg beaten with milk and vanilla. Beat well by hand 1 minute.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare a 10-inch spring-form pan by greasing with 1 tablespoon of the butter.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup of the bread crumbs to coat.
In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook the potatoes until just easily pierced with a knife, about 20 minutes.
Drain immediately.
In large bowl, mash the potatoes, blending in 8 tablespoons of the butter.
Keep the potatoes light and fluffy.
In a saucepan, heat the milk just to simmering.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugars, butter, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in medium bowl.
Mix in flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Mix ground beef, bulk sausage, cooked rice, salt, pepper and well-beaten eggs together well.
Form into patties.
Bake in 450° oven for 20 minutes.

title: summer fruit pie
directions: Stir lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk into Cool Whip. After mixing, add rest of ingredients. Then fold in this mixture into 2 deep-dish prebaked pie shells. Don't add Cool Whip until last. Don't mix any more than you must. Chill 3 hours before serving.

title: pfeffernuesse frosting
directions: Combine egg white, honey and anise seed in bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating after each addition with electric mixer.
Place 12 to 14 peppermints in bowl, coat all sides and place on wire rack.

title: buttermilk corn muffins
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a small bowl and stir well. Make a well in center of mixture and add buttermilk, egg and oil. Stir until dry ingredients are just evenly moistened.
Fold in corn.
Spray muffin tin with vegetable spray and spoon batter 2/3 of the way full into pan.
Bake 425° for 18-20 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice potatoes in large bowl.
Add celery, onions and eggs.

title: teenie wienies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and simmer on low.
Add meats and simmer until hot.
Great in crock-pot.

title: chicken rice pilaf
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients together for 30 minutes.
Skim off fat.
Measure 1/2 cup fat into saucepan.
Brown noodles into melted fat.
Add rice; mix well.
Add chicken broth.
Cover; simmer for about 40 minutes.
Bone chicken and add to rice.

title: apple date muffins(low-fat)
directions: In large bowl, combine whole wheat and all-purpose flours, bran, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon; stir in dates.
In another bowl, beat egg with sugar and oil; stir in milk and apple. Pour into flour mixture and stir just enough to moisten, being careful not to overmix.

title: fetuccine supreme with seafood
directions: Beat cream cheese and 1/4 cup margarine on low speed of mixer until blended. Add parsley, basil and pepper.

Mix well. Add boiling water. Beat until mix is smooth. Cook fettuccine according to package directions. Rinse in warm water. Drain and set aside. Saute garlic in 1/4 cup margarine in small skillet until tender. Combine garlic mixture and warm noodles, tossing gently. Add cream cheese mixture, seafood and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Toss gently. Place in serving dish and sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: brown bean chowder
directions: Brown beef with chopped onions.
Drain meat and place in a large sauce pan.
Add pinto beans, tomato soup, water and chili powder.
Simmer for one hour.

title: williamsburg cheese and olive balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°, 10 minutes before cheese balls are to go in.
Grate cheese and allow to soften at room temperature. Combine cheese, butter and paprika.
Mix well into flour by hand until pieces of cheese disappear and mixture is smooth.
Cover and let stand for 15 minutes.
Take about 1 teaspoon of dough and flatten to 1 1/2-inch circle.
Place a well drained olive in center of dough and bring edges together.
Roll gently between palms.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Chill 10 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: twice baked potatoes and broccoli
directions: Bake potatoes and cook broccoli.
Mash overcooked broccoli, then mash scooped out interior of baked potatoes.
Thin with a little milk and season with salt and pepper.
Add broccoli to potatoes and mix well.
Repack potato skins and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until hot.

title: cherry pie
directions: Fill pastry with cherries.
Mix dry ingredients and sprinkle over cherries.
Dot with butter.
Add top crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: swedish mazarin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter an 8-inch cake pan.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add egg and butter; mix and work dough until smooth.
Line pan with dough.
Spread with a thin layer of jam. In medium size bowl, knead butter, sugar and almonds into a smooth paste.
Add eggs, one at a time and blend thoroughly.
Put on top of jam.
Bake for about 40 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: honeybee ambrosia
directions: Pare oranges; cut into thin slices. Peel banana; cut into thin slices. In serving bowl, mix fruits carefully. Stir together orange juice, honey and lemon juice in a separate bowl. Pour over fruit in bowl. Sprinkle coconut on fruit. Serves 4 to 6.

title: lasagna
directions: Simmer the first 10 ingredients.
Use a large size pan, put in layers, noodles, layer of sauce, layer of cheese and repeat.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool 15 minutes to make easy cutting.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a greased tube pan.
Cook in a 350° preheated oven.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Let stand in pan for 5 minutes and then turn it out to cool.

title: lemon pie-filling mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl and mix well.
Put into a 1-quart airtight container and label as Lemon Pie-Filling Mix.
Store in a cool, dry place and use within 6 to 8 months. Makes about 4 1/4 cups of mix.

title: apple cake
directions: Grease and flour sides, bottom and middle of angel food pan. Mix all ingredients listed with hands.
Put in angel food pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar before baking.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: cabbage with caraway
directions: Remove major section of core from the cabbage.
Leave just enough to hold the head together.
Slice the head into wedges about 1 1/2-inches thick.

title: brown bread (1920)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fill pans half full. Bake at 345 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: monster cookies(cookie of the year, 1977)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a very large bowl with your hands.
Use an ice cream scoop to drop on cookie sheet.
Leave room between cookies.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: basting for lamb roast
directions: Combine; heat but don't boil.
Baste lamb every 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion, garlic, oregano and salt, stirring to separate meat. Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
An additional 1/2 cup cheese may be added to meat mixture.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove the chicken from bones.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Mix dressing with butter.
Sprinkle half of dressing in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread a layer of chicken and celery.
Mix both cans of soup with chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Spread the remaining dressing over top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: marble cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate in the top of a double boiler.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix seasoning in oil.
Pour over crackers.
Mix well.
Heat in ovenproof container at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed pork chops with wine sauce
directions: Sprinkle chops inside and out with salt and pepper.
In heavy skillet, heat 3 tablespoons butter, add onion and celery.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Add bread cubes, fennel and parsley. Remove from heat.
Add cream to moisten mixture.
Stuff chops.
In Dutch oven, melt remaining butter.
Add chops and brown.
Add wine to 1/4 inch depth.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Transfer chops to platter.

title: simply superb pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs, sugar, corn syrup, vanilla and butter.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 45 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between outside and center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons flour with ginger; coat pork.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet.
Fry pork until brown.
Remove from skillet.
Add water to reserved pineapple juice to equal 1 cup.
Shake remaining flour with the syrup/water mixture in tightly covered container. Stir flour mixture, vinegar, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce into fat in skillet.
Heat to boiling; stir constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Reduce heat; stir in sugar, salt, pepper and pork.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add pineapple, green pepper and water chestnuts; cook 10 more minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: broccoli noodle soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add 6 cups water and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling until cubes are dissolved.
Gradually add noodles and salt and continue boiling. Cook uncovered for 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli.
Cook 4 more minutes.
When broccoli is tender, add milk, cheese and pepper. Cook until the cheese melts.
Makes 4 quarts or 12 servings.

title: chicken vesuvio
directions: Coat chicken pieces with a mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Heat 1/2 cup oil in a large skillet. Add chicken pieces and brown on all sides.
Put into
a large shallow baking dish.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil and garlic until garlic is lightly browned.
Add Marsala and parsley.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken in baking dish. Bake at 325° about 45 minutes or until chicken is tender, turning only once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grilled turkey
directions: Cut turkey into four 1/2-inch slices.
Place in shallow dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over turkey.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Grill turkey 3 to 4 inches from hot coals, about 10 minutes, turning once.

title: parmesan chicken(298 calories per serving)
directions: Place each chicken breast between 2 sheets of waxed paper. Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Combine bread crumbs, 1/4 teaspoon basil and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in egg.
Dredge in bread crumb mixture.

title: m and m cookies
directions: Blend sugars, Crisco, vanilla, and eggs in a bowl. In a separate bowl, combine flour, salt, and soda; mix. Add flour mixture to sugar mixture. Mix till well moistened (dough will be stiff). Pinch off a small amount and roll into a ball. Place balls on ungreased baking sheet and add 3 or 4 M & M's to top. Gently press top of cookie to set M & M's and spread cookie dough.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in an uncovered 1 1/2-quart dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together and top with 1 package Waverly wafers or soda crackers mixed with 1 stick of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon bites
directions: Wrap chestnuts in bacon half-strips and pin with toothpicks. Place standing in oven pan.
Cook at high temperature (425°) until bacon is well rendered but not crisp or burned at top edges (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Drain excess grease from pan.
Mix remaining ingredients for sauce.
Baste each piece well and return to oven. Use ample amount of sauce for good basting.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes and repeat basting. Cook 3 to 5 more minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add soup and water.
Stir.
Add broccoli and Cheez Whiz.
Stir well.
Add chicken.
Put rice in casserole.
Pour mixture over it.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: peanut butter krispy treats
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil. Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Put in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan and cool.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; bake in 3 round cake pans in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apple slices in well-greased baking dish.
Mix ingredients with fork, then sprinkle over apples.
Pour melted butter over top, then sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
No brown sugar or oatmeal required for this delicious fall treat.

title: almond meringue cookies(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add skim milk powder.
Mix well.
Add extracts and sugar substitute.
Drop cookies by spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.
Remove cookies from cookie sheet and dust with cinnamon. Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.
One cookie equals 32 calories.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Add remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake about 8 to 10 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: magic meat balls
directions: Pour mixture over meat balls and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve over rice or potatoes.
Also makes a great meat loaf or an appetizer.

title: strawberry divinity
directions: Bring sugar, corn syrup and water to boil in heavy saucepan, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and continue cooking, stirring only occasionally to hard ball stage (252°). Beat egg whites until fluffy. Add jello to egg whites, beating until mixture forms peaks. Pour hot syrup in thin stream into beaten whites, beating constantly. Beat until candy loses gloss and holds shape. Fold in coconut and nuts. Pour into greased pan or drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and layer sliced carrots, onions, potatoes and rice.
Pour soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use 2-quart casserole.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Cook
sugar, salt, cornstarch, flour, boiling water and egg yolks
in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly. Just before
it	is
thick, add 1/4 cup lemon juice and grated rind. Pour
into	baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites, adding 2 tablespoons sugar
for
each egg white.
Place meringue on pie filling and brown in oven at 350°.

title: pear salad
directions: In medium bowl, mash pears; stir in cream cheese until blended. In small saucepan, bring reserved juice to boil, pour into medium bowl.
Sprinkle gelatin over hot juice, pour in 1 cup cold water and stir into pear mixture.
Whisk in whipped topping.
Spray 6 cup mold with nonstick spray, pour mixture into mold.
Chill until set about 4 hours.
To serve, run tip of knife around edge of mold; unmold onto serving plate.
Garnish with mint, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: french dip sandwiches
directions: Place roast in slow cooker.
Add water, soy sauce and seasonings.
Cover and cook on high for 5 - 6 hours or until beef is tender.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Top with 1/2 cup toasted, slivered almonds (optional). Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: salmon stew
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in about 2 cups water in large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add salmon (skin and bones removed).
Add remaining ingredients, plus 2 cans of water.
Cook over low heat until potatoes are soft.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash 3 overripe bananas with sugar and egg.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Add melted butter.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 loaf pans 45 minutes at 350°.
Nuts can be added or sprinkled on top.

title: corn mexican casserole
directions: Brown onions, bell pepper and ground beef.
Add 2 tablespoons chili powder, then mix tomato paste and creamed corn, salt and pepper.
Simmer mixture for 25 minutes.
Add little water, if needed.
Cook 1 bag egg noodles; drain.
Add layer of noodles and layer of meat mixture.
Cover with grated sharp cheese.
Cook at 350° in oven for 30 minutes.

title: noodle and sausage casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water and drain.
Brown sausage with the onions and celery.
Mix the noodles, sausage, onions and celery with the soups.
Put into a buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You may top the dish with Parmesan cheese.

title: enchilada
directions: Brown ground beef with onion. Drain the grease.
Mix in a bowl the taco sauce, enchilada sauce and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix half of the mixture with meat.
Take the shells and put 2 spoons of meat. Roll up and push to end of pan.
Repeat until meat and shells are used.
Spread cheese across top and add rest of sauce mixture over top.
Cook in oven until cheese has had time to melt.

title: crisp coconut cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugars gradually, beating until fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture.
Add cereal and coconut; mix well.

title: taco dip
directions: This is a layered salad served with taco chips.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken and eggs.
Add wine and herbs.
Then add chicken and eggs.
Top with crushed potato chips. Do not use potato chips until ready to bake.
Store in refrigerator before baking.

title: bran muffins
directions: Add raisins and baking soda to boiling water.
Cool.
Mix in huge bowl:
flour, salt, sugar, all-bran or Fiber One, bran flakes and chopped walnuts.
In another bowl, beat eggs, sour milk and oil.
Blend and add to cooled raisin mixture and add to dry ingredients.
Mix. Fill greased muffin tins about 3/4 full. Sprinkle top of each one with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes.
Makes about 55 muffins.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all
together
and	drop in deep fat with teaspoon. Let come to top and brown.

title: baked spinach with bacon
directions: Place a layer of spinach in a buttered 2-quart baking dish. Next, place a layer of tomatoes, sprinkling of onion, small amount of chili sauce, crumbs, salt and paprika.
Then make a layer of cheese; repeat until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle more crumbs on top.
Arrange slices of bacon over top of dish and bake at 350° until cheese melts and bacon is crisp, 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: spritz
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in egg, almond extract and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Press out from cookie press.
Bake at 400°.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Take first three ingredients and mix in saucepan.
Boil good for 1 minute.
Put flour and sugar in bowl.
Add hot mixture over sugar and flour.
Beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well for 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour in greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Generously grease casserole dish with margarine and slightly flour.
Mix and pour in ingredients. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Let broccoli thaw; separate in bowl and add onion, pepper, celery and rice.
In a saucepan, combine soup, Velveeta and margarine and heat until cheese melts.
Stir into broccoli mixture; pour into buttered casserole and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: maple butterscotch brownies
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and maple flavoring.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour and baking powder to egg mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brownies test done.
Cool.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Prebake 10 inch pie shell.
Saute vegetables in butter until crisp but not soft.
Drain well and add seasonings.
Place tomato slices in bottom of prebaked pie shell.
Add vegetables.
Spread mayonnaise and cheese mixture over vegetables.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut thin slice from stem end of each pepper.
Remove seeds; rinse and cook in enough boiling water to cover for 5 minutes. Drain.
Cook hamburger and onion in 10-inch skillet until lightly browned; drain.
Stir in salt, garlic powder, rice and 1 cup of the tomato sauce; heat thoroughly.
Stuff each pepper with hamburger mixture; place in ungreased baking dish 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers.
Cover and cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Melt butter or bacon grease in iron skillet or baking dish.

title: squash pickles
directions: Pour 1/2 cup salt over vegetables in ice water.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.

title: forgotten stew
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients into 3-quart casserole in layers as listed.
Mix the sugar, salt, tapioca and tomato juice and pour over top of layered ingredients.
Top with 1 can of mushrooms, if desired.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: chicken purleau
directions: Cook chicken and onion until tender.
Take chicken off bone. Add rice to chicken broth and cook 10 minutes.
Then cut chicken and sausage into small pieces and add to broth and rice.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is done.

title: refrigerated cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Slice onion.
Heat remaining ingredients to a boil.
Put cabbage and onions in bowl in layers.
Pour liquid over this while hot.
Let stand in covered bowl until cool, shaking it occasionally to mix.
Refrigerate for 2 or 3 hours or overnight before serving.

title: chili-corn pie
directions: Cook and stir hamburger, onion and garlic until meat is browned; drain.
Stir in tomatoes (with liquid), corn, beans, chili powder, salt and marjoram.
Heat to boiling.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole or 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: crab shrimp bake
directions: Mix together.
You may add a little horseradish, if desired. Put in a casserole.
Melt several tablespoons of butter and combine with 1 cup of bread crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: e-z corn pudding
directions: Use a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add eggs, corn and milk; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Start checking pudding at 45 to 50 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Knife should come out clean.

title: pineapple slush
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Process until slushy.
Serves 1.

title: mama's corn bread dressing
directions: Make corn bread according to directions on the package.
After it has baked and cooled, chop corn bread and bread slices into 1/2-inch cubes.
In a large bowl, mix breads and vegetables.
In pot, combine broth and spices and bring to a bowl.
When broth has cooled, add egg and whisk together, then pour over bread mix and stir gently. Press dressing into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Can be doubled as needed.
Serves 8.

title: laura's artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Serve warm.
Best served with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli italiano
directions: In a large skillet, combine all ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
(I found it took longer.)

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together. Combine other ingredients and bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot artichoke parmesan spread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place artichoke hearts in center of a clean kitchen towel, gather up ends and twist firmly to extract all water.

title: yellow party cake seven minute frosting
directions: In double boiler top not over heat, combine sugar, egg whites, corn syrup and salt.
Add cold water.
Beat 1/2 minute at low speed of electric mixer to blend.
Place over boiling water (upper pan should not touch water).
Beating constantly with electric mixer, cook about 7 minutes or until frosting forms stiff peaks. Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat about 2 minutes more or until of spreading consistency.
Spread on cake at once.

title: sweet and sour asparagus
directions: Mix all ingredients except asparagus in a saucepan.
Heat until mixture comes to boil.
Place asparagus in bowl, pour hot liquid over and refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese strata
directions: Cut 12 "doughnuts" from bread.
Fit scraps and holes in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place cheese over bread and add layer of broccoli.
Then layer ham and onion.
Arrange bread doughnuts on the top.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over top. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove cover and bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until set in center.
Serves 12.

title: roasted spareribs and kraut
directions: Put ribs in roasting pan.
Add sauerkraut.
Cut apple and onion fine.
Mix with sauerkraut.
Put on top of slab of ribs. Add water over the ribs and kraut.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake in oven for 2 hours at 325° or until golden brown.

title: catfish fingers with three sauces
directions: In a bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat together milk and egg.
Cut catfish into thick sticks.
Dip sticks into milk mixture, then in cornmeal.
Heat oil to 350°.
Fry sticks in small batches; drain.
Serves 8.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 475° until knife comes out clean.

title: jennifer's potato casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese.
Melt a little and add to potatoes and maybe some milk.
Add garlic to taste, about 1/2 teaspoon.
Mix and pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Cook until cheese melts (20 to 30 minutes).
Can be frozen.

title: creamy lemon meringue pie
directions: Brown pie crust
first.
Beat egg yolks, milk and lemon juice until creamy.
Pour into crust.

title: fudge
directions: Mix ingredients.
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour immediately 9 x 13 pan lined with foil.
Refrigerate.
Cut!

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients together; spread over melted butter.
Spoon butter over top of bread mix.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti 10 minutes; rinse and drain.
Add chopped pepper, onion and celery.
Stir in Salad Supreme and Italian dressing.
Keeps for weeks in refrigerator.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add pineapple with juice.
Then add blueberries and gel.

title: tea cakes
directions: Slowly add flour and make up like biscuits and roll out in small balls.
Press flat.
Cook at 400° until brown.

title: butterscotch peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in top of double boiler.
Place over hot, not boiling, water until butterscotch melts; stir until blended.
Add milk and stir just until blended.
Spread in greased or foil lined 8-inch square pan. Chill until firm, then cut into squares.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon; fold in mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: freezer meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine eggs, milk, bread crumbs, onion, parsley, salt, thyme and pepper.
Add ground beef.
Mix well.
Shape into 60 (1 1/2-inch) meatballs.
Place on 2 (15 x 10 x 1-inch) baking pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Cool.
Wrap in three 20 meatball packages.
Freeze up to 6 months.
Serves 12.

title: moist yellow cake
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 35 to 40 minutes.

title: herb-roasted chicken with tomato-basil sauce
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Pull neck skin to back and twist wing tips under.
Brush with 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Combine Italian seasoning, parsley, garlic and onion salts; sprinkle some seasoning mixture inside and rub remaining outside of chicken. Tie legs together.
Place chicken, breast side up, on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Roast, uncovered, in 375° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cover and let stand 15 minutes before carving.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Break biscuits in small pieces.
Mix in milk, sugar and spices.
Spray glass baking dish with Baker's Joy.
Pour mixture into dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: raspberry salad
directions: May add a drop or two of red food coloring, if so desired.

title: zucchini con queso soup
directions: Melt margarine and add onion and garlic.
Saute until tender. Add zucchini, seasonings and flour.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Add broth and milk with whisk.
Simmer with chilies, uncovered, 5 to 7 minutes until thickened and chilies are cooked. Add tomatoes and heat through.
Add cheeses and remove from heat. Serve with taco chips.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs until light and fluffy.
Add the sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly, but well. Combine the flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and allspice.
Add to the egg mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour. Cool on rack.

title: old time bread pudding
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, salt, milk, water and vanilla.
Place toast in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour mixture over toast.
Let sit 10 minutes, then sprinkle top with 4 teaspoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Place crackers in an aluminum roasting pan.
Drizzle 1/2 cup of oil over crackers.
Sprinkle seasoning mixture over crackers. Place crackers in a large plastic bag.
Put garlic powder, lemon pepper and dill weed in bag.
Shake bag to mix ingredients.
Dump crackers back in aluminum roasting pan.
Bake in a 200° to 250° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick fruit delight
directions: In a large bowl, combine fruit.
Mix sour cream and sugar. Pour over fruit.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Serves 6.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix vegetables in bowl.
Bring sugar, vinegar and oil to a boil in a saucepan.
Pour over vegetables; mix well.
Chill overnight.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Blend together mayonnaise, curry powder, salt and pepper.
In a large bowl, mix together chicken, celery, apple and onion.
Add the dressing and mix well.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Toss sugar, flour and cornmeal lightly with fork.
Add rest of ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until top is golden brown. Cut when warm.
Makes a thick 9-inch pie, shimmery and golden inside.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with a spoon.
Refrigerate.

title: okra cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon into hot fat. Fry until browned.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Grate cabbage in large bowl and stir in the ingredients.
Will keep in closed containers or jars in the refrigerator for several weeks.
Great with hamburgers, hot dogs, barbecue or vegetables. Yields 5 quarts.

title: bill's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done but not mushy.
Let cool, peel and dice.
Add butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Mash slightly and add in onion, dill pickles and hard boiled eggs.
Add salad dressing and mustard to taste and mix thoroughly.
Slice hard boiled eggs for top of salad and sprinkle with paprika.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: judy's gooey bars
directions: Mix lemon cake mix, egg and margarine.
Spray a 9 x 12-inch baking dish with non-stick vegetable spray.
Press mixture into bottom and sides of pan.

title: cream of zucchini soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden.
In saucepan, combine all ingredients except milk; cook until zucchini is tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Puree in blender and add evaporated milk.
Return to stove just long enough to heat, but not boil (will curdle if boiled).

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, vanilla, lemon and eggs.

In a separate bowl, sift together salt, flour, baking powder and soda. Combine bananas with sour cream and nuts in separate bowl. Combine the butter mixture with dry ingredients and add banana mixture.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, yogurt and strawberries.
Put in pie crust and freeze.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream lard, sugar and eggs well.
Add buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Stir in flour until stiff enough to knead on floured dough board.
Roll out and cut with your favorite cutter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° until done (lightly brown).

title: baked salad
directions: Boil shrimp in a little water and salt.
Combine all other ingredients except bread crumbs and margarine.
Mix shrimp and mixture and pour into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over it, then pour margarine on crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: black walnut brittle
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and water in large skillet or saucepan. Bring slowly to 230° (or soft ball stage without candy thermometer).
Add walnuts and continue cooking to 300°. Stirring constantly, remove from heat; add butter, vanilla, soda and salt.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into well-buttered cookie sheet.
When cooled completely, break into pieces.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Cook ground meat until browned, drain excess fat.
Add all 4 cans of soups (no water)
Mix well.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Cover the top of casserole with french fries. Bake at 350 degree for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: apricot bundt cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; add eggs and fold in all other ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan for approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Check after cooking for 45 minutes. Varies in different ovens.

title: buckeye bars
directions: Put peanut butter and butter in microwave to soften. Stir in graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar. Mix well. Pat mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. On low heat, melt chocolate chips. Stir in oil. Pour over crust and refrigerate for several hours. Cut into bars.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Top with crushed strawberries or other fruit along with ice cream.
This was Ora Slaubaugh's recipe.

title: caramel-peanut apples
directions: Wash and dry apples.
Insert craft sticks into stem end of each apple; set aside.
Combine caramels and water in a medium bowl; microwave at High for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes, or until smooth, stirring after each minute.
Dip 2/3 of each apple into hot caramel sauce, turning to coat.
Scrape excess sauce from bottom of apples; roll coated bottoms in peanuts.
Place on wax paper coated with cooking spray.
Store in refrigerator.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes before serving to allow caramel to soften.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and mash them and mix all ingredients.
Save enough cheese and Ritz to go on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add sugar while beating.
Fold in chocolate chips, nuts and flavoring.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix into ball and cover with pecans.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: candied nuts
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter until forms soft ball.
Add dash of salt and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts.
Drop onto foil and separate.
Let cool.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Slowly blend in flour and vanilla.
Gently fold in potato chips.
Drop by well-rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Wet a fork to prevent sticking; flatten cookie gently.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until just barely browned.
Cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: festive holiday salad
directions: Combine 1 large can of crushed pineapple (juice included) with one small (4 serving size) box of instant pistachio pudding.
Add about 5 ounces (1/2 bag) of miniature marshmallows and one 8 ounce container of whipped topping.
Add about 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Chill for several hours and serve with turkey, pork or anything!

title: hearty tuna casserole
directions: Drain and flake the tuna.
Set aside.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and rinse in hot water.
Combine noodles with the tuna, celery and green onions.
Blend in sour cream, mustard, mayonnaise, thyme and salt.
Spoon half the mixture into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with half the zucchini.
Repeat layers.
Top with the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with the chopped tomato.

title: crab meltaway
directions: Mix well.
Spread on muffins.
Freeze 30 minutes.
Broil until puffed up and bubbling.

title: chicken salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: In large bowl combine mayonnaise, ginger and salt.
Stir in chicken, grapes, celery, green onions and walnuts.
Cover; chill. Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: greek bean soup
directions: Boil beans in water for 1/2 hour.
Add oil, tomatoes, onions, garlic, celery, carrots, salt and pepper.
Cook for 4 hours.
Add green pepper after 2 hours of cooking.
Add olives after 3 hours of cooking.
Serve hot.

title: never fail pickles
directions: Put powdered alum in gallon jar.
Slice cucumbers to fill jar. Cover with cold water.
Let sit 24 hours.
Drain and rinse 2 or 3 times.
Put pickling spices and salt in jar with pickles and cover with pure vinegar.
Let sit for 6 weeks in cool place, then drain off vinegar and add sugar.
Let sit 3 weeks.
Ready to eat.
Never seal jar.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: hot barbecue sauce
directions: Blend ingredients and simmer for about 20 minutes, then baste meat while cooking.

title: ground beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck in shortening.
Drain.
Combine boiling water and onion.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add mushroom soup, salt and pepper.
Cover bottom of 1 1/2 quart casserole with layer of thinly sliced potatoes.
Cover with thin layer of meat, top with soup-onion mixture and continue alternating layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes to one hour or until potatoes are tender.
Extra water may be added if mixture is too dry.
Casserole may be prepared ahead of time.

title: harvest special
directions: Saute ground beef with onion and peppers in skillet until crumbly.
Add seasonings.
Layer half the corn-ground beef mixture and tomatoes in 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: baked round steak
directions: Saute finely diced onion in shortening until lightly browned. Remove from skillet.
Cut meat in serving size pieces; roll in flour and brown in fat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove meat from skillet and add enough water to make at least 2 cups thin gravy.
This will thicken during baking.
Add ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and A.1. sauce and season with salt and pepper.
Place meat in small roaster or casserole dish; spread onion over meat and add gravy.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over rice and herbs.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Place rice in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add soup, mushrooms and liquid, water and seasonings.
Mix and set aside. Saute onion in oil until transparent.
Add to casserole.
Brown meat and add to rice mixture.
Chill.
When ready to bake, cover and bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry cream crunch
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Mix together flour, salt, cinnamon, coconut and oats and add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts to mixture.
This mixture should be crumbly.
Place 2 1/2 cups of mixture in an ungreased 8 x 12-inch baking dish and bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: mom's bonbons
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar, blend thoroughly.
Beat in vanilla and salt, add food color to tint.
Refrigerate covered 1 hour.
Shape into balls using rounded teaspoon each.
Roll in coconut.
Place on wax paper and refrigerate until firm.

title: cobbler
directions: Put fruit in bottom of baking dish.
Dice bread slices; put on top of fruit.
Mix the remaining ingredients; pour over bread. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle coconut on top of crumbs.
Add chocolate chips, then butterscotch chips.
Pour 1 can condensed milk on top.
Cover with chopped nuts; press with spoon so they won't fall off.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, Miracle Whip, eggs, water and cinnamon, mixing well on medium speed, using electric mixer.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when inserting into cake.
Cool.
Spread frosting over cake.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In a skillet, fry hamburger meat, onion and pepper until meat is brown and onion and peppers are tender.
Add zucchini, tomato sauce and corn.
Cook until zucchini is tender on low heat.

title: banana dessert(fat-free)
directions: Cut bananas in half lengthwise; cut those halves in half.
In a nonstick skillet heat apple juice.
Add bananas and honey; add cinnamon.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add lime juice.
Stir well.
Serve immediately.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: "divinity"
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook over heat to boiling (260° on thermometer).
Remove from heat.
Immediately beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Gradually pour mixture in a thin stream over egg whites, beating at high speed about 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat until candy starts to lose its gloss.
Add nuts and cherries.
Quickly drop in spoonfuls or line pan.

title: rice dressing(100 servings)
directions: Saute ground meat with vegetables (except green onion tops) until tender; drain. Add remainder of ingredients (except green onions); mix well. Add green onions last and cook till tender.
