Add Kitchen Bouquet for color. Mixture will be thick (may need to add a little water). Cook 4 rice cookers (10 c. each) of rice. Add mixture to cooked rice while both are hot. Makes 100 or more servings.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown beef and onions; drain.
Place in a loaf pan.

title: 15 minute stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from meat and slice into strips.
Melt butter and brown meat.
Add 2/3 cup water and mushrooms.
Stir in soup mix. Heat to boiling.
Blend sour cream and flour; add to hot mixture. Cook and stir until thickened.
Sauce will be thin.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix with hands all of the ingredients.
It is best to mix this and let stay in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° or 375° for 1 hour in a preheated oven.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
I bake my loaf in a Pyrex loaf pan; spray pan with Pam or oil.

title: chip beef bread dip
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan and heat (low heat).
Cut middle out of bread making a bowl.
Pour mixture into bread bowl.
Cut remaining bread up into cubes for dippings.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter, add to graham cracker crumbs.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan (greased).
Add remaining ingredients to pan, 1 at a time.
Creating a layer for each ingredient, end with sweetened condensed milk, then chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add tomato juice, tomato paste, tomato sauce, garlic salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat, 2 to 3 hours.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Alternate layers of noodles, sauce and cheese in a baking dish.
Bake until hot.

title: apple crisp
directions: Bake at 350° until done (40 minutes).

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Mix tapioca and milk in top of a double boiler.
Heat, stirring constantly, until milk comes to a boil.
(Do not let boil.)
Remove from heat and add vanilla and sweetener.
Chill and serve.
Yield:
1 serving.
Carbohydrate 19 g, protein 8 g, fat 1 g, calories 198.
One serving = 1/2 bread starch exchange, 1 cup whole milk exchange.

title: mud pie
directions: Crush Oreo cookies for crust; place in pie pan. Add a layer of ice cream; add fudge sauce. Whip the cream; add sugar and vanilla; spread on top of fudge sauce. Grate chocolate on top. Freeze and serve.

title: lazy man's pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients into dough.
Melt butter in pan or casserole that you plan to cook pie in.
Pour mix in.
Add fruit and juice.
Bake at 350°-375° for 35-40 minutes.

title: chicken and green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and sprinkle cheese on top, covering well. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: easy microwave lasagna
directions: Crumble beef into microwave colander.
Cook on High 3 minutes. Break up clumps of meat with fork.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes. Combine sauce and water in mixing bowl; add meat and stir.
Mix Ricotta cheese, egg and parsley in small bowl.
Place 1/3 meat mixture in bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Place 4 noodles on top of sauce.
Spoon 1/2 Ricotta cheese on dry noodles.
Add 1/2 Mozzarella and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Repeat with next 1/3 sauce, 4 noodles and cheeses.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High 8 to 10 minutes.
Cook on 50% (Medium) 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Add flour and dry ingredients.
Make hickory nut size balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet. With fork, make crisscross. Sprinkle sugar. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: breakfast pie
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp. Remove to paper towels. Drain, reserving 2 tsp. drippings. Stir reserved drippings into cornflakes; set aside. In a bowl combine the eggs, milk, cottage cheese, cheddar cheese, onion, salt and pepper until blended. Stir in hash browns. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with bacon and the cornflake mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove from fridge 30 minutes before baking. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45-50 minutes.

title: amazing raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 or 8-inch round pans.
In large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat first 10 ingredients for 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently, or 300 strokes by hand (batter is thick). With spoon, stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Spoon batter into pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tester in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove, cool and ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: pizza muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Split muffins in half and place in a shallow baking dish.
Spoon spaghetti sauce onto muffins.
Top each muffin with a slice of cheese.
Trim cheese to the same size as muffin.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is browned slightly on the edges.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Add Bisquick and sausage.
Shape into balls. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
May be frozen before baking. Thaw thoroughly and then bake.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Debone cooked chicken, cut in small pieces and set aside. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
In large skillet, heat oil and saute onions over medium heat.
Blend in cornstarch, water, soy sauce and black pepper.
Let thicken slightly.
Add bean sprouts, water chestnuts, bamboo shoots, garlic, mushrooms and chicken; simmer on low heat for about 10 minutes.
Add celery; simmer 5 minutes longer.
Celery should be crunchy.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick, easy 'n light
directions: Skin the chicken parts.
Hold pieces over dry or lightly greased skillet and sprinkle both sides generously with the soy sauce.
Place in skillet.
Cover tightly; cook at medium heat for approximately 15 minutes.
Turn.
Cover and cook 15 minutes longer.
Remove lid; brown on both sides in own gravy.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer rolls, sausage, hash browns and cheese.
Put eggs in bowl with salt and pepper.
Beat with a fork and pour egg mixture over layered ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple and chicory salad
directions: Fill a large bowl with water and add the lemon juice.
Core the apples but do not peel them.
Cut them into chunks, put in water and juice.
Drain and add to salad and celery.
Stir together sour cream, yogurt, horseradish, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over salad and then add walnuts.
Serves 4.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into three greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: freezer pickles
directions: In large bowl, mix cucumbers, onion and salt.
Add 2 trays of ice cubes and let set for 2 hours.
Drain and set aside.
Do not rinse.

title: 3 soup goulash
directions: While macaroni cooks, saute onion in small amount of oil; add beef.
Stir and brown.
(Drain grease.)
Mix all the soups with the hamburger; add the cooked macaroni and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Stir in cranberry juice and cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Shape cream cheese into 18 balls.
Sprinkle sugar on strawberries; stir.
Pour 1/3 cup thickened jello into mold; arrange cheese balls on top.
Spoon strawberries over cream cheese balls.
Pour remaining jello over strawberries.
Chill until firm.

title: ham and cheese stromboli(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat baking sheet with cooking spray. Combine honey and mustard.
On floured surface, roll dough to 11 x 15-inches.
Brush with mustard mixture.
Layer 1/2 the ham, leaving 1-inch edge on 15-inch side.
Fold in 6-inches toward the center.
Fold over again to cover the filling.
Pinch side seams. Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Slice in 1-inch slices.

title: stuffed macaroni shells
directions: Cook shells in water, 2 tablespoons salt and 1 tablespoon olive oil for 15 minutes.
Drain on waxed paper.
Mix remaining ingredients and stuff shells.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix the last 5 ingredients and pour over the vegetables.

title: pecan squares
directions: Combine flour and powdered sugar in a medium bowl. Cut in butter with a pastry blender until crumbly. Press mixture evenly into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Combine sweetened condensed milk and next 4 ingredients. Pour over prepared crust. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden. Cool and cut into squares. Yield: 4 dozen.

title: potato candy
directions: In large pan, mix mashed potatoes and 10x sugar; mix.
Mixture will become watery before becoming thick; dust wax paper with 10x sugar and rolling pin with 10x sugar.
Press mashed potato mix onto wax paper.
Roll out with rolling pin.
Spread with peanut butter, creamy or chunky, to desired thickness.
Lifting paper at one end, roll into roll; wrap in wax paper and place in freezer. After 2 hours it can be cut with knife.
Roll does not freeze so hard it cannot be cut without thawing.

title: martha's company casserole
directions: Cook noodles (drain).
Cook hamburg; stir in tomato sauce. Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, green onion and green peppers in a casserole dish.

title: coconut balls
directions: Cook butter, egg, sugar and dates until mushy.
Let cool. Roll in crushed nuts and Rice Krispies.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
Add cranberry sauce while the jello is still hot so it will dissolve.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Put into 3-quart (9 x 13-inch) casserole.
Make at least 1 or 2 days ahead.

title: corn meal johnny cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and molasses together.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Stir in meal and flour.
Mix well.
Pour in small Bundt pan or loaf pan and bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Wet hands with cold water and form meat balls about the size of a quarter.
Fry until well browned in deep fat or oil.
Turn into a saucepan.
Put 1 can undiluted cream of chicken or celery soup over them.
Simmer, covered, for about 30 minutes.
Soup will form delicious gravy.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice in long pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Chop up onion over rice.
Place pork chops or chicken on top of rice. Spread mushroom soup on top of meat. Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes or until done.

title: easy chocolate cherry cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Do not use beaters.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Test for doneness by inserting toothpick into cake.
When toothpick is dry, cake is done.
Frost with chocolate fudge frosting.

title: sugar custard
directions: Pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 300° until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: peppercorn chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken in pan; add butter.
Sprinkle with peppercorn. This should be in non-stick pan.
Turn once in about 5 minutes. Remove chicken and keep warm.
Add sherry or orange juice, whipping cream and tarragon leaves; stir until glaze is thick.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Cook 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: skillet irish bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a large bowl.
Cut in butter or margarine with pastry blender.
Add caraway seeds, eggs, milk, light cream and raisins.
Mix well.
Spoon into well-greased iron skillet (10 1/2-inch size).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack before slicing.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, salt.
Put layer of crumbs in greased baking dish.
Cover with layer of apples.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Continue until all ingredients are used.
Have layer of crumbs on top.
Pour melted fat over crumbs.
Cover dish.
Bake at 375°
(moderate oven) 40 minutes.
Remove cover the last 10 minute to brown the top.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: banana pudding with sugar substitute
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler.
Add cornstarch, Equal and beaten egg yolks.
Do not overcook.
Let lightly thicken.
Cool. Add flavoring.
Cover with meringue.
Bake until brown.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over melted margarine.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in buttered casserole, except potato chips.
Sprinkle chips on top.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: make-ahead raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Batter may be stored in refrigerator up to 8 weeks.
Do not stir after refrigerated before baking.

title: dried fruit oat muffins
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Prepare muffin cups as above.
In bowl, mix first 5 ingredients; stir in oats and dried fruit.
On wax paper, mix dry ingredients and stir into batter just until moistened.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden.
Makes 12 muffins, 168 calories each.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, prepare a dressing of the oil, vinegar and sugar mixed together. Mix in the green beans, carrots, celery, green pepper and onion into dressing and keep the vegetables pressed down with a plate on top. Refrigerate overnight. Drain well before serving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato bake
directions: Layer potatoes in greased casserole dish.
Heat soup and stir in cheese.
Pour over potatoes. Bake about 1 hour in a 350° oven, testing for doneness with a fork.

title: crispy treats
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large saucepan over low heat, stir together first 3 ingredients.
Stir constantly. Bring to boil and boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add cereal and toss to coat well.
Press into pan and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: sauteed chicken livers and shrimp
directions: In large skillet, melt butter over low flame; add garlic, chicken livers, onion and wine.
Cook on smallest flame until livers are almost done.
Add shrimp, mushrooms, salt and pepper. Finish cooking on high flame until shrimp are done (do not overcook), about 5 minutes.
Add parsley and serve.
Serves 4.

title: crab and pasta
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in onion and mushrooms; cook over low heat until soft.
Remove mushrooms and onion.
Stir in crab meat.
Add the sherry; cook over low heat for 3 minutes (stir constantly).
Add cream, mushrooms and onion; cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in cooked pasta.
Remove from heat.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 4 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of pretzel mixture.
Place in refrigerator for 30 minutes.

title: rigatoni and peppers
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Add garlic, mushrooms and oregano.
Cook over low heat 5 to 7 minutes.
Combine spaghetti sauce with 3/4 jar of hot peppers and sauce in large baking dish. Add cooked onions and mushrooms.
Cover and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cook rigatoni for 15 minutes.
Add to dish of sauce.
Cover and let sit for 30 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese and heat to melt. Can be refrigerated/frozen and reheated.
Can use fewer hot peppers.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage; boil and remove leaves.
Trim down thick ridge in center of leaf.
Saute onion in butter.
Bring rice to boil. Rinse.
Mix ground meat, rice and onion.
Add salt and pepper. Put sauerkraut in bottom of roaster.
Put meat mixture in leaf to about 3/4-inch.
Roll up.
Put in layers with sauerkraut in between.
Add diluted tomato soup.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour gradually, then add milk, vanilla and salt.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 70 minutes.

title: oriental celery
directions: Cook in small amount of salted boiling water the celery, cut into 1-inch slices.
Cook until crisp done (about 8 minutes). Drain.
Add water chestnuts, drained cream of chicken soup and pimento.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Combine melted butter, almonds and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle casserole.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: broccoli casserole #8
directions: Cook
broccoli (frozen or fresh) for 5 minutes or until tender;
drain well.
Chop broccoli into small pieces; fold in the remaining
ingredients.	 Put
in
buttered
casserole. Sprinkle
top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked manicotti
directions: To make sauce:
In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot oil, cook onion, garlic and oregano until onion is tender.
Stir in soup, water, tomato paste, Parmesan cheese and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, or until desired consistency, stirring occasionally.
Discard bay leaf.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes, using a greased and floured tube pan.

title: blackberry wine
directions: Cover blackberries with boiling water; let stand for 2 hours. Squeeze through a cheesecloth and add sugar to the liquid.
Pour liquid in an open jar.
Cover with cheesecloth
and let stand until fermenting ceases.
At this time, bottle.

title: pound cake
directions: Place sugar, eggs, milk, flavorings and rind in mixing bowl. Mix slightly to combine.
Pour half into second mixing bowl containing shortening, baking powder, salt and flour. Mix well on high with small mixer and on medium speed with large mixer.
Add remaining liquid mixture.
Mix slowly and only until well combined.
Pour into greased and floured (Baker's Joy) tube pan. Bake at 250° for 40 minutes.
Raise oven temperature to 325° for 60 to 80 minutes (depending on oven). Bake until cake tests done. Let sit out of oven 10 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt butter and pour in mixture of flour and pecans.
Mix well.
Press in bottom of rectangular baking dish.
Brown at 350° for 20 minutes and let cool.

title: western baked beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Place onion and vinegar in saucepan.
Cook 20 minutes.
Assemble.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes, then bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Mix oleo, sweetener and egg.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour and applesauce.
Fold in raisins and oats or bran.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Can be made into a cake.

title: taco twist soup
directions: In a large pot, brown meat with onion and garlic. Drain. Sprinkle chili powder and cumin over meat.
Cook and stir 30 seconds. Add other ingredients except cheese and chips.
Bring to a boil, stirring often. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes or until pasta is done.
Place in bowls and top with cheese and chips.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Bring butter or margarine and the eggs to room temperature. Grease and flour the bottom and sides of a 10-inch Bundt pan or two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans; set aside.

title: easy breakfast(for a crowd)
directions: Beat eggs
lightly.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch
baking
dish.
Set dish in cookie sheet.
Fill cookie sheet with water.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
(I make the night
before
and
refrigerate.
Bake in the morning, it tastes better.) Great with sweet rolls.

title: polka daters
directions: Mix chopped dates and hot water (cool).
Beat until creamy butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift and stir in gradually flour and baking soda.
Stir in date mixture, vanilla and half of chocolate bits.
Spread in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with half of chocolate bits and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat in vanilla and eggs. In another bowl, sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to sugar-egg mixture. Blend well.
Stir in 1/2 cup of M&M's (save rest for decorating). Drop 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate with remaining M&M's.
Bake on center rack at 375° for 10 minutes. remove with spatula to wire racks.
Cool completely.

title: lasagna or spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat; remove from pan.
Saute onion, garlic and green pepper.
Add meat.
Add stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, sugar, salt, pepper, oregano, basil and mushrooms.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Can be doubled.
Can be frozen.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In a large saucepan, brown meat with oil.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, basil, savory salt and onion soup mix.
Cover; simmer for about 15 minutes.

Prepare celery, celery leaves and carrots, then add to simmering mixture and continue to cook for 30 more minutes. Add macaroni and carrots; simmer for an additional 30 minutes. Serve in bowls topped with Parmesan cheese.
French bread goes well with this.

title: breakfast cheesecake
directions: Spread one can crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine next 4 ingredients and spread on rolls in pan.
Spread other can of rolls on top of cream cheese mixture.
Beat egg white and brush on top.
Mix sugar and nuts and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Remove skin and bones from cooked chicken.
Tear in pieces and mix in a large bowl with all other ingredients (saving some cheese to sprinkle over finished casserole).
Pour into a large baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp oreganata
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put raw shrimp in lemon juice and let them sit in it.
Melt butter and add all ingredients to butter and pour over shrimp.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes; broil for 3 minutes.

title: charlie's favorite chocolate cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, combine cream cheese and sugar; beat well.
Blend in cocoa, scraping sides of bowl and beaters frequently.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Blend in whipping cream.
Pour into crust and bake 35 to 40 minutes. Center will be soft, but will set upon cooling.
Cool to room temperature.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with pie filling.

title: grandmother wolfe's chicken pot pie
directions: Stew chicken in water, parsley, salt and minced onion.
Cool. Cook in 3 cups chicken stock:
carrots, potatoes, celery and 1 tablespoon minced onion.
Drain vegetables and cool; reserve stock. Dissolve corn starch, salt and milk in broth.
Cook until thickened.
Cool.
Divide meat, broth and vegetables and fill pie shells.
Cover with pie crust.
Bake at 400° for one hour.

title: chili beans
directions: Fry hamburger and onions together until brown, then mix all together.
Cook over low heat for 3 to 4 hours, stirring often.

title: monterey baked salad
directions: Saute meat with garlic and onion powders in a lightly greased skillet, about 10 minutes or until done.
Blend salt, Tabasco, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Add this mixture and remaining ingredients except corn chips to ground beef.
Turn mixture into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with corn chips.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie filling
directions: Mix together the Jell-O and flour and stir in the rhubarb. Put in unbaked pie shell. Bake for 60 to 65 minutes at 350°.
Top with a mixture of the sugar, flour and oleo.
Let cool 3 hours and serve.

title: frozen cranberry salad(dessert-like)
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise together until fluffy. Add cranberry sauce, drained pineapple and pecans, and mix well. Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into a large mold or in individual muffin tins, lined with paper liners.
Freeze until firm.
Serves 12 or more.

title: strawberry jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil in mixing bowl.
Add beaten eggs.
Combine and sift dry ingredients.
Add to mixture, alternating milk and dry ingredients.
Add jam and vanilla; mix well.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch or larger baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven until top springs back when touched.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening and margarine. Mix milk, egg yolks and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
This will make 3 pie crusts.

title: country "fare" spuds
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes according to package directions, reducing water to 2 1/4 cups and omitting salt.
Blend cream cheese into hot mashed potatoes.
Add onion, egg, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Transfer to
a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Tastes just like pierogi!

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown meats in frying pan until done.
Drain on paper towels. Put meat in a crock-pot.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine; pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned in 350° oven.

title: cold vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent roll on baking sheet.
Pinch together to form solid crust.
Bake according to directions, then cool.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread over crescent roll.
Cover with favorite vegetables and cheese and chill.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: chicken, broccoli, rice casserole
directions: Melt butter; add onion and celery.
Let simmer while preparing remaining ingredients.
Drop broccoli in boiling salted water long enough to separate (do not cook); drain.
Mix soup, rice, milk, sugar, Cheez Whiz, broccoli and chicken in a large bowl.
Add celery and onion.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.
Uncover about 15 minutes until it's bubbly in the middle.

title: sausage noodle casserole
directions: Fry sausage; break into small pieces.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Drain drippings.
Cook egg noodles as directed and drain.
Mix soup with milk.
Add thyme and pepper to taste.
Add mixture to sausage.
In casserole dish, layer half of noodles, half of mushroom-sausage sauce.
Cut cheese in quarters and top.
Repeat layers.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: apple crumb pudding
directions: Grease baking dish 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Put apples in dish. Cream butter and sugar; work in flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for 20 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: sour cream chicken or turkey nachos
directions: Combine sour cream, process cheese and sauce in saucepan; stir over low heat until process cheese spread is melted.
Stir in chicken or turkey.
On serving platter, layer half of chips, process spread mixture, lettuce, tomato and olives; repeat layers. Top with additional sour cream, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in condensed milk, lemon juice, rind and, if desired, a few drops of yellow food coloring. Pour into prepared crust.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Chill.
Spread with whipped cream topping. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat whites until stiff.
Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add nuts and coconut.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 floured and greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and frost cake with the following frosting.

title: play dough
directions: Mix liquid ingredients in saucepan on medium heat.
Mix dry ingredients and add slowly to liquid mixture. Continue to cook until mixture forms a ball or looks to be the consistency of mashed potatoes. Scrape onto the counter and knead.
Store in airtight container.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. Put sliced cheese on top soon after removing from oven.

title: chicken breasts italian
directions: Soak boneless chicken breasts overnight in evaporated milk. Blot with paper towels and coat in mixture of Italian crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Roll up and wrap a strip of bacon around each breast.

title: sugar-free millionaire pie
directions: Brush crust with egg yolk.
Bake in oven at 350° for 4 minutes. Combine pineapple (juice included) and sour cream.
Stir in pudding.
Fill crust and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: pickled peaches from canned peaches
directions: Bring to boil 1 minute; cool and pour over peaches.
Let stand in refrigerator for a couple days.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix sugar, pumpkin, shortening and orange peel. Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.Stir in raisins and/or nuts.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Split each chicken wing in the joint and discard the tips. Deep fry at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or bake in oven at 400° for 25 minutes or until crispy.
Drain the wings.
Mix the melted butter, hot sauce, lemon juice and honey.
Dip the wings in the sauce.
Serve with celery sticks and Blue cheese dressing.

title: rolled chicken washington
directions: Cheese Filling:
Cook mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes. Blend in flour; stir in cream.
Add salt and pepper; cook and stir until mixture becomes very thick.
Stir in cheese; cook over very low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Turn mixture onto pie plate; cover and chill overnight.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Pop the corn; make about 4 cups.
Melt butter in a large pan; add vanilla and marshmallows and pour over popcorn.
Add M&M's and peanuts.
Mix well and press down firmly in a greased tube pan. Place in freezer about 15 minutes.
Turn out on cake plate.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain fruit (save juice).
Heat juice from fruit and pour into gelatin and dissolve.
Cool completely and add Coke.
Half or quarter cherries and remove pits.
Chip up frozen cream cheese. When gelatin is thick, add fruit, nuts, cheese and cherries. Chill until firm.
Slice and serve.
Makes 16 servings.

title: "white pizza"
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare pan, grease with Crisco. Spread dough evenly.
Coat oil on surface of dough.
Spoon Ricotta cheese all over dough.
Add Mozzarella cheese evenly.
Add grated cheese.
Sprinkle pepper, oregano and garlic powder to your taste. Bake in 425° preheated oven until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: baked ham
directions: Wrap ham in aluminum foil.
Place skin side down and start in a cold oven.
Bake 25 minutes per pound at 325°.
Before last hour of cooking, remove skin and excess fat.
Score and stick whole cloves in ham and rub with the mixture of flour, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Return to oven and bake 1 hour.

title: chocolate peanut butter desserts
directions: Mix milk into peanut butter in small bowl.
Stir in Cool Whip. Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes (until thickened).
Spoon pudding-Cool Whip mixture alternately into 6 parfait glasses.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip.

title: cranberry apple relish
directions: Finely grate outer rind and set aside.
Peel off and discard white membrane.
Slice the orange into 8 pieces.
Place a fourth of cranberries and orange slices in a food processor or blender; process until evenly chopped.
Transfer to a large bowl; repeat until all cranberries and oranges have been chopped.
Stir in the rind, apples and sugar.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight.
Yield: 6 cups.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Put peas on bottom of pan.
Pour corn on top of peas.
Brown chopped meat and lay on top of vegetables.
Cover with cooked mashed potatoes.
Bake at 375° until mashed potatoes brown.
Remove from oven and serve.

title: mochi with strawberry centers
directions: Combine mochiko,
water
and
sugar in a microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on
High	for
4	minutes.
Turn pan and mix. Microwave for another
minutes.
Mix until smooth (adding a couple of spoonfuls of water helps).	Sprinkle generous amount of katakuri on	work surface (cookie sheet works well).
Place mochi on katakuri,
then
sprinkle
more
on
top, as mochi is flattened. Slice into 3 x 3-inch squares.
Wash, hull and dry strawberries. With
damp hands, wrap tsubushian around strawberries, then
wrap mochi around tsubushian.
Place in cupcake liners.	Eat within 48 hours.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix all.
You can put 2 cups crushed corn flakes on top.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: chili verde
directions: Brown and drain off pork, then add the rest of the ingredients and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice boiled potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients and refrigerate a couple of hours before serving.

title: k-bars
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and peanut butter to a boil over low heat. Pour the mixture over cereal.
Put mixture in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Melt butterscotch chips and chocolate chips and spread on top.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine butter, cola and oil in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan or your favorite greased and floured pan. Bundt pan works good.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cake cool thoroughly before attempting to remove from pan.

title: southwestern chicken
directions: Spray a 9-inch pie plate with nonstick spray coating.
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together chicken, corn and green chili peppers.
Spread mixture in pie plate.
In the same bowl, stir together eggs and milk.
Beat in flour, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is set and lightly browned.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 2 to 3 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: microwave hot bean dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in a 1-quart casserole.
Spread chili over cream cheese. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Microwave for about 2 minutes until bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Cook stew beef 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients with the exception of cream-style yellow corn. Cook 1 additional hour.
Add cream-style yellow corn and cook extra 15 minutes.
Stir almost constantly to keep cream-style corn from settling to the bottom and scorching.

title: olive-filled cheese balls
directions: Cream together cheese and butter.
Blend in flour and cayenne. Drop teaspoon of dough around an olive, covering it completely. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 25 balls.

title: egg 'n things
directions: Saute green beans and chopped onion in butter.
Beat eggs and pour over other ingredients.
Cook until done.
Serve with pineapple or other fruit.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Grease an 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan well.
Cut dates into 4 pieces using kitchen scissors.
Drop into a 3-quart mixing bowl. Add boiling water, brown sugar and butter.
Stir thoroughly.
Let cool.
Stir flour and measure.
Resift 3 times with salt and soda. Stir egg into date mixture.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Turn into prepared pan and bake like Apricot Nut Bread, about 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Arrange cookie slices, slightly overlapping on aluminum foil covered 14-inch pizza pan; press edges to seal.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; remove from foil onto serving plate.
Combine cream cheeses, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended. Spread over crust.
Arrange fruit on cream cheese mixture.
Glaze with combined marmalade and water.
Chill.
Cut into wedges. Calories 215, fat 8 gm and sodium 240 mg.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: calypso pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of the pudding mixture over cracker crumbs.
Add another layer of crumbs.
Add another layer of pudding.
Pour chocolate icing over top.
Chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease shallow pan and line with dressing mix.
Boil squash in water until tender. Drain and mash.
Mix squash, sour cream, onion and soup.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour this over layer of dressing. Sprinkle dressing mix on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: blueberry squares
directions: Blend cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over crust. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Add pie filling.
Serve with ice cream.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix and beat by hand real well: eggs, sugar, flour, milk, vanilla, and margarine. Spread dried peaches on bottom of pie shells. Pour egg mixture on top of peaches. Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes or until brown.

title: praline strips
directions: Bring to a boil on high, sugar and butter.
Turn to low.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add pecans.
Pour over graham crackers which have been placed in bottom of baking pan with sides.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Cut and place on wax paper.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine ground beef, flakes, 1 cup water, onion, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 24 balls.
In skillet, brown meat balls in butter.
Remove.
Mix flour with butter in skillet.
Add remaining 1 cup water.
Stir to form white sauce. Return meat balls to skillet.
Cover tightly and simmer 10 minutes.

title: cooked chocolate icing
directions: Cook chocolate, sugar, syrup, salt and milk until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Stir constantly to prevent burning. Remove from heat and add butter.
Let cool without stirring until lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until spreading consistency.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla extract.
Stir in salt and flour until well blended.
Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray and pour mixture onto pan.
Pat entire mixture over the surface, sprinkling flour where needed to keep the mixture from sticking to your fingers.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, being careful not to over brown.
It will be a soft dough.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle chocolate pieces over cookie.
When melted, spread over all.
Cut bars while warm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars, egg and peanut butter together.
Add dry ingredients and flavoring.
Make out into walnut size balls. Press out with fork on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Can freeze dough.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake biscuit quarters in bag of cinnamon and sugar. Boil butter, Karo & brown sugar for 1 minute. Put quarters in greased bunt pan. Pour syrup over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Turn pan over onto large plate with lip. Serve warm.

title: pickled okra
directions: Place okra in jar.
Boil vinegar, water and salt for 5 minutes.
Place hot pepper, garlic and dill in each jar.
Pour boiling vinegar over and seal.

title: deviled eggs
directions: With a sharp knife, cut the eggs in half and lay them on a platter.
Carefully remove the egg yolks, leaving the whites intact, and add them to all the other ingredients in a bowl, mixing well.
Spoon the mixture evenly into the egg whites.
Makes 12.

title: greek vegetable couscous
directions: Combine water and broth; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; add couscous.
Cover and let stand until liquid is absorbed (about 5 minutes).
Coat skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and saute 1 minute.
Add zucchini, tomatoes, and onion.
Saute 2 minutes.
Add garbanzo beans and next 4 ingredients.
Cook until heated.
Top with cheese, olives and parsley.

title: world's best coconut pie (or chocolate)
directions: For Coconut Pie:
Add 1 cup coconut.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and oil.
Mix well.
Stir in zucchini and add dry ingredients.
Mix well and stir in nuts, raisins and pineapple.
Pour in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tests done.

title: quick casserole
directions: Place crabmeat in bottom of buttered casserole.
Add mushroom soup (undiluted).
Add beans.
Use liquid from beans to rinse the soup can and add to the casserole.
Top with onion rings.
Heat through in a 350° oven.
Do not let onions burn.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer on med. heat until all vegetables are tender.

title: done buttered biscuits
directions: Soften butter and mix with yogurt and Bisquick.
Spray small muffin pans with Pam.
Fill pans 3/4 with dough.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 11 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.
Freezes well.

title: pumpernickel dip
directions: Put in hollowed-out loaf of pumpernickel bread.
Save bread pieces for dipping.

title: black forest cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Line the bottoms of 2 (8-inch) round layer cake pans with wax paper.
On a sheet of wax paper, sift together the cocoa powder, flour, 1 cup of the granulated sugar and the salt.
Set aside.

title: freezer coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrot and pepper in large bowl.
Add salt. Let stand for 1 hour.
Drain excess liquid.
Boil sugar, vinegar, water, mustard and celery seed.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Cool. Put into containers and freeze.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Cook mushrooms and green pepper in
margarine over medium heat; blend in salt and pepper.
Cook over slow heat, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in bouillon, milk, water and mushroom liquid.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 1 minute, then stir in chicken and pimento; heat through.
Serve over rice or toast.

title: cracker candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk and bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients and let stand for a few minutes.
Beat and pour into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: el rancho beans
directions: 1. Brown ground beef & onions in 1/4 c. Salad oil.
2. Combine remaining ingredients in baking dish or pan.
3. Bake at 400° for 30-40 minutes.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Mix together peanuts, pretzels, Rice Chex, Corn Chex and Wheat Chex.
Melt white chocolate bark.
Pour over other ingredients. Pour out on wax paper.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: jam kolaches
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add flour, mixing well.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Cut with a 2-inch round cutter.
Place 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Spoon 1/4 teaspoonful of jam on each cookie.
Fold opposite sides together, slightly overlapping edge.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cherry liqueur
directions: Put all ingredients together in a large covered container or decanter (glass is best).
Shake it occasionally as it stands. Let it stand until the candy is dissolved or from 4 to 6 weeks.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in water.
Remove the chicken and cook the vermicelli in the chicken broth.
While the vermicelli is cooking, saute the onion and bell pepper in the butter.
When the vermicelli is done, do not remove it from the water.
Instead, add the sauteed vegetables, Ro-Tel, cubed cheese and all other ingredients, including the chicken which should be cubed.
Once the cheese is completely melted, pour the mixture into a large casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine
ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: krum-kake
directions: Put about 1 soup spoon batter in hot Krum-Kake iron.
Bake until brown on both sides.
Roll quickly around stick or cone-shaped form.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Heat water, sugar and cornstarch until thickened.
Add Jell-O. Let cool and add fresh strawberries.
Put in baked pie shell and cool until set.
Top with whipped topping.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain the beans.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over beans and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day remove from dressing with slotted spoon, put into another bowl and serve.

title: banana pie
directions: Crush graham cracker.
Put in pan. Slice the bananas and arrange on cracker crumbs.
Cream the cheese.
Beat with the milk until thick. Pour cream cheese mixture over bananas. Chill well.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450° and grease the bottom of muffin cups. With hand mixer, beat the eggs slightly. Add milk, flour and salt and beat just until the mixture is smooth and runny. Fill muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake 5 minutes, then lower oven to 350°. Bake 15 to 25 minutes longer until brown on top.

title: summer pasta salad with ham
directions: Prepare salad as directed on package except decrease water in dressing to 1 tablespoon and mix in sugar, vinegar and catsup. Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Layer all ingredients as listed in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool. Cut into squares.

title: dutch cheese fondue
directions: Pour the wine into a 2-quart fondue dish (or any 2-quart flameproof enameled casserole).
Drop in the garlic; bring to a boil over high heat.
Let the wine boil briskly for 2 minutes, then with a slotted spoon, remove and discard the garlic.
Lower the heat so that the wine barely simmers.
Stir constantly with a table fork.
Add the cheese, a handful at a time, letting each handful melt before adding another.

title: marinated carrots
directions: This recipe makes quite a lot and proportions can be changed to suit.

title: apple cinnamon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Beat Crisco, sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon rind until light and fluffy.
By hand stir in flour mixture. Do not overmix.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spoon into loaf pan.

title: lil westover's molasses cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and molasses.
Add egg and mix well. Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together. Form in balls. Dip in white sugar and place, sugar side up, on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
If you did it right, there will be large cracks on the cookies when they are done.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Add first 4 ingredients together and boil for 3 to 4 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in nuts.
Stir until mixture hardens. Spoon onto wax paper.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat; add onions, celery, mustard, brown sugar, catsup and salt.
Simmer on low and stir off and on for 1 hour or until well done.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Saute ground meat; drain.
Cook 10 to 12 servings of mashed potatoes following directions on the box.
Grate or slice the cheese.
In a large casserole dish, pour meat, tomato sauce and onion in the bottom.
Add mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle the cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon delight
directions: Combine flour, oleo and nuts; press into bottom of cake pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let crust cool completely.
Mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar; spread over cooled crust.
In large bowl, mix instant pudding and milk; blend until pudding mixture.
Spread this over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.
Top lightly with finely chopped walnuts.

title: boston style baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine mustard, salt, sugar and ketchup in a medium bowl.
Add onions and corn.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bacon. Bake for 40 minutes or until bacon is cooked.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: special deviled eggs
directions: To Boil the Eggs:
Put eggs in water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and turn off heat.
Let set 20 minutes.
Remove eggs and cool in cold water.
They will never be tough!

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix cabbage and salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze moisture out of cabbage.
Add carrots and peppers.
Mix remaining ingredients for dressing; bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Cool until lukewarm. Pour over slaw; mix well.
Pack into freezer containers; cover and freeze.
This slaw thaws quickly, and any leftover slaw may be refrozen.
The cabbage stays crisp.

title: chocolate goodie
directions: Melt oleo in long Pyrex dish, mix in flour and nuts and pat out
to cover bottom of dish.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned (about 25 minutes).
Cool slightly before adding next layer.

title: artichoke crab casserole
directions: Layer in casserole artichoke, crab and mushrooms.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, salt, margarine and Karo in pan.
Heat to boiling. Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Pour over corn and mix well.
Spread into a shallow pan.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes(kids love them...adults, too.)
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a medium bowl.
Add the wet ingredients. Blend with mixer for 1 to 2 minutes. Pour cake batter into cones, 1/2 full. Bake at 300° to 350°
for about 20 minutes. Test to see if top springs back when touched.
Frost when cool and dip icing in nonpareil sprinkles.
Makes 10 to 12.

title: "no roll" sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Add to flour mixture.
Chill for 2 hours.
Shape into balls, then flatten with fingers or bottom of small glass with a design on bottom. Dip bottom of glass into flour before flattening balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Very crisp!

title: prune cake
directions: Place oil and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Beat well; add eggs and beat until creamy.
Sift flour three times with soda, salt and spices, then add to mixture alternating with buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in chopped prunes and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Let cake cool before icing.

title: peach and blueberry crisp
directions: Combine rice, peaches, blueberries and 2 tablespoons of sugar. Coat 6 individual custard cups or 1 1/2 quart baking dish with cooking spray. Place rice mixture in cups or baking dish, set aside.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Bring cauliflower, onion and celery to a boil in 2 cups water. Simmer until tender.
Mix together flour, milk, salt and butter. Stir into cauliflower.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly, adding more milk if it is too thick.
Garnish with parsley and paprika.

title: the green eagle dish with eggs
directions: Cook spinach until all water is gone.
Add grease, salt and pepper.
Stir in onion.
Let spinach cook dry.
Add eggs last.

title: molasses drop cookies - jelly center
directions: In large mixer bowl, mix molasses and soda.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Make hole in center and fill with jam or jelly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Reserve broth.
Cool, bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Saute mushrooms and add to chicken.
Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Cut pimentos into small pieces.
Add chicken, mushrooms, noodles, pimentos, both soups and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together.

title: brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small mixer bowl, cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Spread batter evenly in a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Cut into wedges in pan.
Wrap and pack for lunch.

title: greek style shrimp
directions: In a saucepan, heat oil.
Add garlic, onion and green pepper; saute for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and wine; simmer until thick and pulpy.
Stir in shrimp; cook for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until shrimp is pink and firm.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into serving dish; sprinkle with Feta cheese.
Serve with rice, mixed with melted butter and pine nuts, if desired. Or, serve with Pilaff Greek Style.

title: turtle cake
directions: Make cake according to directions.
Take 1/2 of cake mix and add 1/2 can Eagle Brand milk and 1 stick butter.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-Os in hot and cold waters.
Add lemon juice and pie filling.
When mixture is set, mix sour cream and powdered sugar and pour over top.

title: no knead dinner rolls
directions: Blend together sugar and shortening; add hot water.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add eggs, flour and salt.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Stir down, cover up to 4 to 5 days.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness, cut with biscuit cutter and fold over and place on cookie sheet.
Brush with melted butter.
Let rise until double and bake at 350° until brown, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate buttermilk sheet cake
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Mix sugar with flour.
In pan on stove, bring to boil water, butter and cocoa.
Add hot mixture to sugar mixture and beat.
Mix together egg, soda, vanilla and buttermilk. Add to batter.
Pour into greased jelly-roll pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: chokecherry wine
directions: Dissolve yeast in a little warm water.
Combine all the ingredients plus yeast in a crock or large new waste basket.
Stir twice a day for 20 days.
Let settle for 10 more days and siphon into bottles.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Put 3 cups milk in medium saucepan and heat.
Divide eggs and beat yolks.
Add small amount of milk from saucepan.
Mix.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Mix.
Add to milk and stir and cook to boiling (at least 3 minutes).
Add vanilla and coconut (save some for top of meringue).
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with meringue and coconut.
Bake at 400° until brown.
This can be used for banana cream pie, too.

title: banana sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, then bananas and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Gradually stir into cream mixture.
Blend in sour cream. Stir in oats and pecans.
Turn into greased and floured 9-cup Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes. Let cool 10 minutes.
Unmold.
Drizzle with lemon-flavored confectioners sugar glaze.
Serve warm.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder, salt and water.
Drop this dough by teaspoonfuls into hot chicken broth or beef broth.
Turn these dumplings as they cook.

title: hershey's chocolatetown cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

In a large bowl, cream butter or margarine, shortening, brown sugar, sugar, eggs, corn syrup, water and vanilla. Beat well. Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a separate bowl; add to creamed mixture. Beat well. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until very lightly brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Take a large, round loaf of pumpernickel bread and cut the center out; put the dip in the bread.
Dip is also good with wheat crackers.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix juice with the sugar, flour and margarine. Cook until thick. Cool and mix with fruit. Top with Cool Whip.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs, salt, baking soda, vanilla and pineapple (with juice) in a large bowl.
Stir until well blended. Pour into a sprayed 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a large double boiler, melt butter; saute onions, garlic and celery until celery is tender and onions are translucent.
Add flour to make a roux, stirring constantly so it does not burn. This mixture should be thick.
Once roux is ready, slowly add clam juice and stir constantly to eliminate any lumps from the roux and obtain a smooth mixture.
Add thyme, pepper, potatoes and bay leaf. Simmer until potatoes are tender and add clams.
Simmer for 5 more minutes and remove from heat.
Remove bay leaf; add heavy cream and serve.

title: chili cheese fries
directions: Put chili on first and then cheese and fries.

title: deep fry batter for vegetables or cheese curds
directions: Combine cornstarch, flour, baking powder, salt and pepper. Stir in water and egg.
Beat until well blended.
Heat oil in a deep fryer to 375°.
Dip vegetable pieces or cheese cubes in batter and fry in hot oil.
Fry 3 or 4 curds at a time otherwise cheese melts out of curd.
Stir batter occasionally, as you dip. If batter is too thick, add a little water.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Make biscuits in usual manner.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: polynesian chicken salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Blend mayonnaise, sour cream and seasoning.
Pour over chicken and toss lightly.
Chill.

title: winter rainbows
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Beat butter with brown and white sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients slowly.

title: mounds
directions: Mix eggs, butter, pecans, sugar, flour and cocoa.
Pour into a 9 x 14-inch glass pan (cake pan size).
Bake 25 minutes.
Combine coconut and condensed milk.
Spread evenly over first layer.
Bake 10 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips over coconut layer.
Bake 5 minutes.
Let cool completely; cut into bars, then refrigerate.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.

Combine flour, soda and oats; add to creamed mixture. Press half of the crumb mixture into the bottom of a cookie sheet. Spread preserves over pressed crumb mixture. Sprinkle remainder of crumb mixture over preserves.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.
Yield: approximately 4 dozen.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg.
Cream mixture until fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients until mixture is smooth.
Blend in milk.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Take glass and wet bottom.
Dip in sugar and flatten cookie.
Very good without the work!

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender until smooth and serve.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Pour crackers in a large bowl and mix with the combined dry dressing mix, dill weed and garlic powder.
Pour oil over crackers and stir thoroughly until well coated.
Put in a plastic bag and tie securely.
Shake the contents.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine reserved juice and raisins in a small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain.

title: grandma's irish soda bread
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Mix the dry ingredients.
Work in the butter.
Then beat eggs and milk together and then mix into the dry.
Put into 2 round cake pans.
Let mixture stand in the pans for 20 minutes before cooking.

title: no knead dinner rolls
directions: Pour water in bowl.
Dissolve the sugar and yeast.
Beat in the egg and oil.
Add the flour and salt.
With large spoon, beat this spongy dough until it is elastic and smooth.
Cover with clean, damp towel and put somewhere warm to rise for 1 hour.
Drop the dough into greased muffin tins, filling each half full. Should have enough dough to fill 18 medium cups.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap (greased first so dough won't stick); let dough rise again until doubled, 30 to 45 minutes.
Fifteen minutes before ready to bake, turn oven to 400°, then bake rolls 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
When done, remove from tins.

title: snow cream
directions: Beat egg white until fluffy.
Stir in sugar gradually, one table spoon at a time.
Then stir in milk and vanilla.
Gently stir in snow and serve at once.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: marshmallow bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
In large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, 1 cup butter and vanilla; blend well.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake 15 minutes; remove from oven.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Return to oven; bake 5 to 6 minutes until marshmallows are slightly melted.
In top of double boiler, melt chocolate chips and 3 tablespoons butter.
Add water and stir until smooth.
Drizzle over marshmallows.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix shortening, margarine and sugar.
Blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and lemon or orange extract, then baking powder.
Add flour and milk alternately ending with flour (add in thirds).
Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 70 minutes.
Cool for 25 minutes, then invert on a rack.

title: frozen chocolate toffee nut squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of a small cookie sheet with crackers, salt side up.
Place butter and margarine in saucepan over low heat and stir until melted.
Add brown sugar and stir until ingredients are well blended and sauce like consistency.
Pour the brown sugar syrup evenly over the crackers, smoothing with a wooden spoon.
Place in oven for 6 to 8 minutes (mixture will bubble on top of saltines and form a toffee layer underneath).
Remove cookie sheet from oven, realign the saltines with wooden spoon.
Pour chocolate chips evenly over saltines and put back in oven for 2 minutes to melt.
Remove from oven and quickly spread melted chips as if you were frosting a cake. Sprinkle evenly with nuts and place in freezer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from freezer and cut into squares with pizza cutter or sharp knife.
Cover with foil or plastic and store in fridge or freezer.
Makes 30 to 35 squares.

title: candied pecans
directions: Beat egg white until foamy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until stiff.
Take fork and roll pecans in batter.
Place on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 225° for about 30 minutes.

title: coconut pineapple pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix together well and pour into two pie shells.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Beat nonfat milk and flour with water until smooth.
Add tarragon, parsley and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Mix in chicken and vegetables. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with pastry crust or mashed potato topping.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 4 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla; stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, then raisins and nuts.
Grease and flour pans (regular size); bake 60 to 70 minutes in 350° oven. Do not underbake.

title: chicken pie(club member: john waters)
directions: Butter large casserole dish. Put in a layer of chicken followed by a layer of sliced eggs. Mix broth and soup; pour over the chicken and eggs. Mix butter and flour well, then mix with milk. Pour over chicken. Cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil. Cook until desired thickness.

title: frozen mint pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine condensed milk, peppermint extract and, if desired, food coloring.
Fold whipped topping. Turn into crust; cover.
Freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Garnish as desired.
Freeze leftovers.
Makes 1 pie.
Preparation time:
8 minutes.

title: microwave creamed spinach
directions: Press excess moisture out of spinach.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and spinach together and cook for 4 minutes at Medium power.
Cover and let rest for 5 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O as on package.
Melt cheese and marshmallows in hot water.
Combine the two mixtures; allow to cool.
Add drained pineapple, whipped cream and pecans.
Freeze and cut into squares.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients together.
Pour over cauliflower, green pepper, parsley and cucumber; toss.
Refrigerate overnight. Radishes may be added at serving time, if desired.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger in oil.
Shred all vegetables in food processor.
Saute in butter, then add to meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Cool; take off heat.
Freezes very well.

title: party oyster cracker mix
directions: Mix well.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix pineapple and Jell-O.
Heat until Jell-O dissolves.
Mix in buttermilk; add coconut and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate.

title: snickers surprise cookies
directions: Combine the butter, peanut butter and sugars using a mixer on a medium to low speed until light and fluffy. Slowly add eggs and vanilla until thoroughly combined. Then mix in flour, salt and baking soda. Cover and chill dough for 2 to 3 hours. Unwrap all of the Snickers candy. Remove dough from refrigerator. Divide into 1 tablespoon pieces and flatten. Place a Snickers Miniature in the center of each piece of dough. Form the dough into a ball around each candy bar. Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes. (Baking time and temperature may need to be adjusted if using more than 1 tablespoon of cookie dough.) Let cookies cool on a baking rack. In a small saucepan or double boiler, melt the Dove candies and drizzle melted chocolate over the top of each cookie. Makes about 24 cookies.

title: baked natural asparagus
directions: Arrange asparagus in 1-quart shallow casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: paella
directions: Heat oil and saute onion, garlic, pepper and rice for about 5 minutes.
Add broth, salt and saffron.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.

title: crab mornay
directions: Make white sauce of margarine, flour, half and half and stock. Add seasonings, parsley and green onions.
Cook until thick.
Add wine and cheese.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Add a little to beaten egg yolks; then combine sauce and yolks.
Cook 1 minute. Fold crab meat and cook 5 minutes.

title: glory burgers
directions: Put all ingredients in pan.
Cook until meat changes color. Add cheese.
Let it cook until it melts.
Pour mixture into bowl; cover and let it stand for several hours in refrigerator.
Using buns of your choice, brush 1 side with butter and the other with mustard.
Spoon burger mixture onto the bun.
Wrap each bun in foil and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Brown meat in fat about 20 minutes.
Add boiling water and rest of ingredients except carrots, potatoes, 1/2 cup water and 1/4 cup flour.
Simmer about 2 hours until meat is thoroughly done and tender.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Mix cold water and flour.
Remove bay leaves and garlic.
Make a well in center of meat and potatoes and pour in water and flour mixture to thicken.
Cook gently about 5 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: Spread slices of dried beef with cream cheese.
Wrap around a small dill pickle.
Chill and slice.

title: smith island jello salad
directions: Mix pudding and water and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add gelatin and lemonade mix and cool slightly.
Add drained pineapple and orange slices, then add Cool Whip.
Pour into dish and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pasta in a pot
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Brown meat and drain.
Add onion, garlic, spaghetti sauce and tomatoes.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and sherry. Mix well. Add dry ingredients and blend. Add fruits and nuts that have been chopped. Nuts should be broken into fairly small pieces. Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cool.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs, and toss lightly.
Shape into cakes; roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot fat or stuff in baking shells.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Mix all wet ingredients together.
Add in all stuffing mix except enough to sprinkle on top.
Place in buttered casserole dish and bake until bubbly brown at 325°.

title: microwave rice krispie bars
directions: Place margarine in a 1 1/2-quart glass baking dish.
Microwave for about 1 minute or until it is melted.
Stir in marshmallows. Microwave for 1 minute.
Remove and stir.
Microwave again for 1 minute or until marshmallows are melted.
Remove and stir.
Mix in cereal.
Press into the baking dish.
Cool until set; cut into squares.
Yield:
24 to 30 bars.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and let sit in refrigerator overnight for best results. Drop in hot grease, teaspoon at a time.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until firm.

title: chicken breasts with mushrooms and sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook mushrooms in oil until soft.
Add onion and garlic powder.
Add tomatoes, paste and seasonings.
Let simmer for 1 hour.
Add sugar, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Oil baking dish.
Lay chicken in dish.
Pour the sauce with mushrooms over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: applesauce snack cake
directions: Mix and bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Blend cornstarch, flour and sugar. Stir and add to boiling water. Stir constantly for about 5 minutes. Cover mixture and steam 15 minutes.
Add butter and beaten egg yolks, cooking only 2 minutes.
Remove from fire. Add lemon juice and grated rind.
When cool, fill baked pie shell and cover with meringue.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: Cook noodles per directions.
Drain spinach and mix with cottage and Mozzarella cheeses, nutmeg, egg white and Parmesan cheese.
In casserole dish, put a layer of spaghetti sauce and then a layer of noodles.
Spread mix over noodles and repeat layer.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Total calories, 1602.
Total fat grams 45.6.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Place chicken in dish.
Pour in 1 cup rice.
Add onion soup.
Add water and mushrooms.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn chicken, bake 30 minutes longer.

title: stack cake
directions: Use enough buttermilk to make dough soft.
Mix with electric mixer until smooth.
Bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes.
It makes 3 layers.
Pour into cake pans (sort of thin).
The layers will be stacked.
Put apple butter or dried apples between each layer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onions until tender.
Stir in green pepper, celery, chicken broth and soy sauce.
Cook over medium heat.
Add chicken and mushrooms.

title: na-na's chocolate chip giant cookie
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Line two 9- inch round pizza pans, extending foil over edges of pan.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Heat milk slightly and dissolve yeast.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 2 hours.
Cream butter, salt and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Stir this mixture into the yeast sponge.
Add 2 cups flour and mix thoroughly.
Rub top of dough with butter or Crisco and let rise again until double in bulk. Roll about 3/8-inch thick and cut with floured doughnut cutter. Allow to rise about 45 minutes.
Fry in deep fat heated to 365°. Drain on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with sugar or use glaze made by adding about 3 tablespoons water to 1 cup confectioners sugar. Makes 18 to 20 doughnuts.
tags: active dry or compressed yeast cake

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in oil until golden brown with chopped onion and diced bell pepper.
Add parsley, salt, pepper and tomato.
Add warm water and chicken broth.
Simmer for 25 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: eggnog cake
directions: Generously grease and flour Bundt pan or two 10-inch pans. Sprinkle nuts on bottom of prepared pans (about 2 teaspoons in each individual pan; set aside.
Heat oven to 325°.
Put dry cake mix in a large bowl and add eggnog, oil and eggs.
Add rum and nutmeg and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour batter in prepared pans. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Use a cream cheese icing for cake.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Blend in butter and yogurt.
Pour over fruit choice in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Important Note: Don't use electric mixer. Fold all ingredients by hand.

title: yow's yum yum salad
directions: Bring lemon juice, pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/3 cup cold water and add to hot mixture; cool.
Add whipped cream, cut up cherries and cheese.
Let congeal.
Serve on lettuce leaf or add homemade mayonnaise and chopped cashew nuts.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and flour.
Preheat oven to 350°. Beat Crisco and sugar for 1 minute on medium speed.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk; mix well.
Pour into pan; bake for 30 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve with strawberries and whipped topping.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Line pie plate with graham crackers for crust.
Beat egg yolks into milk and lemon juice.
Pour into crust and chill.
Top with meringue before serving.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Press 1/2 of mixture into a rectangular cake pan.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, salt, butter and cocoa.
Bring to full boil. boil for 3 minutes.
Take off stove.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop onto wax paper.

title: corned beef pate
directions: Soften onion in water for 5 minutes.
Flake corned beef with fork.
Add braunschweiger, mayonnaise, vinegar, dry mustard and onion mixture.
Place half the mixture in blender container and blend at medium speed until smooth.
Remove from blender and repeat with remaining mixture.

title: virginia peanut soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add onion and celery. Saute for 5 minutes (do not brown).

Add flour and mix until flour is blended with butter. Add hot chicken broth and cook 30 minutes. Remove from heat. Strain broth. Stir the peanut butter, celery salt, salt and lemon juice into the strained broth. Sprinkle chopped peanuts on soup before serving.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Peel and slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Peel onion 1/4-inch thick.
In a casserole dish, layer ground beef, potato and onion in layers that cover the bottom of dish.
Continue with layers until all ingredients are used.
Mix can of soup with water.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle entire dish lightly with salt and pepper.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours until potatoes stick tender.

title: duncan tavern cheese pudding
directions: In large bowl, toss bread crumbs in melted butter.
Alternate layers of bread cubes and grated cheese in well-greased casserole. Beat egg yolks and mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour over cheese and bread cubes.
Beat egg whites stiff but not dry.
Fold into mixture.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until firm.
Serves 8.

title: cheese cake
directions: (You may need to add a little milk.)

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water; add pineapple, marshmallows and cheese.
When about to set, fold in cream, which has been whipped.
Add nuts.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Place over medium heat and bring to a boil.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and 1 cup nuts, if desired.
Stir until it thickens. Pour into greased platter. Cool before cutting.

title: frosty punch
directions: Mix gelatin and juices according to pkg. and can directions. Combine mixture, add Ginger Ale and sherbet just before serving. Yield, 25 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix with remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: macadamia nut crust
directions: To make vanilla wafer crumbs, add a few at a time to blender and whirl.
Combine ingredients and press in the bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: crumb crust
directions: Crush
crackers with rolling pin on wax paper.
Combine with remaining
ingredients in mixing bowl, stirring to blend well. Press
mixture firmly into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool before filling.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes in 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: whiskey sour slushes
directions: Thaw orange juice and lemonade.
(Do not add water.)
Add lemon soda and bourbon.
Freeze in 1/2 gallon containers.
When ready to use, put in refrigerator to slush.

title: strawberry milkshake
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl.
Blend with a hand blender.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan or muffin pan.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix all in heavy saucepan.
Cook and stir until thick, about 5 minutes.

title: karo crazy crunch
directions: Mix corn and nuts on a cookie sheet.
(May take two.) Combine sugar, butter and syrup in a 1 1/2-quart pan; bring to a boil. Boil 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until a light caramel color.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour over corn; mix to coat and spread out to dry.
Break apart and store in a tightly covered container.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: yellow buns
directions: Cook milk and corn meal (can be white or yellow) until thick. Add butter, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand for 20 minutes.
Then add eggs and flour.
Combine with cornmeal mixture and add enough additional flour (3 to 3 1/2 cups) until a soft bun mix.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Then add bananas and nuts (if desired).
Add milk with soda dissolved in it.
Add flour and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: carolina chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice on	bottom	of dish.
Layer chicken breasts on rice. Spread
soup	over
chicken.	Pour
4 cups water over soup. Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake, covered, at 325°
for
hours. Uncover and cook for 10 minutes.

title: venison steak supreme
directions: Season steak with salt and pepper.
Bake in iron skillet or baking dish.
Combine soup and water.
Pour over steak.
Cover with foil and lid sealing tight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 2 hours.
Do not stir or uncover!!!
Steak and gravy will be ready for table.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All. Mix with other ingredients. Mix cracker crumbs and melted margarine; sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Serve with fresh sliced fruit.
