title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked 9 inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mae's chicken breasts
directions: Spray baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Arrange chicken breasts in dish.
Top each with slice of Swiss cheese. Combine the soups (undiluted).
Sprinkle Stove Top with seasoning over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, covered.
(You can combine soup, Stove Top and seasoning together and pour over top and bake.)

title: jello salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed.
Let thicken.
Beat with mixer. Add pineapple, Cool Whip and pecan pieces.
Keep in refrigerator until used.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and pepper until done but not dry. Drain.
Add seasoning, Cheez Whiz and soup.
Slice top off French bread.
Remove inside and add to meat mixture.
Spoon meat into hollowed out French bread bottom.
Put top back on.
Place in oven until bread is warm.
Remove.
Slice and serve.
Oven temperature, 325°.

title: creamed peas and potatoes
directions: Boil peas and potatoes together until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add milk to almost cover vegetables. Add 2 tablespoons margarine and heat.
Stir in cornstarch and water mixture until thickens.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: breaded veal cutlets
directions: In shallow bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dip veal cutlets in flour mixture.

title: chiles rellenos
directions: Lay rolls flat; overlap perforated edge.
Flatten to 1/16-inch with a lightly floured rolling pin.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch circles. Combine cheese and green chilies.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place 1 teaspoon cheese mixture off center of each circle.
Fold closest edge over to cover cheese.
Fold in both sides, envelope fashion. Roll and place, seam side down, on a baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve immediately with taco sauce.
Makes 32 miniature rellenos.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: Cook until thickened and dogs are piping hot.
Leave dogs in sauce and use toothpicks for serving.
Using regular franks are better, for the ends get all rounded as they cook.

title: plain ole' rice pudding
directions: Put rice in a well-buttered casserole dish with the milk and sugar; place butter sparingly over the top and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: soft pumpkin cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla; beat until light and creamy.
Mix in dry ingredients until well blended.
Add raisins.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Mix all the ingredients together and pour hot grease from bacon over.
Then mix 1 beaten egg, 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/3 cup vinegar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour over salad.

title: gilroy garlic bread
directions: Slice bread lengthwise into top and bottom halves.
Melt or soften butter or margarine.
Mix with Miracle Whip, garlic, cheese and seasonings.
Spread mixture evenly on bread.
Broil until bubbly and just beginning to brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Salt and pepper chicken and dip in melted butter.
Pour excess butter in a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Mix soups and rice and pour in casserole.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour and 5 minutes. Cover with aluminum foil and bake an additional 35 minutes.

title: microwave chili con  queso
directions: Using a microwave-safe container, cut Velveeta into 1-inch chunks and combine with Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Melt in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir at the end of 2 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
In saucepan, mix hamburger, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Then season to taste with salt, pepper, garlic, basil, parsley and oregano.
Cook on medium heat, stirring occasionally.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: pasta fasula
directions: Saute garlic in pan until lightly brown.
Add paste slowly and simmer until pasta cooks down to brownish color; add water a little at a time, then add beans.
Cook pasta al dente; drain and add to beans mixture.
Serve as soup, then enjoy!
Top with grated Italian cheese if desired.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Save egg whites for topping.
Save 1/2 of coconut for topping. Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Make meringue using egg whites and coconut.
Put on baked pie and bake meringue until done.

title: fruit cake
directions: Work flour, baking powder and sugar into the fruit-nut mixture.
Add vanilla and beaten eggs.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: okra croquettes
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, salt and pepper. Stir in egg. Add okra and onion. Mixture is very stiff and does not hold together well. Drop by tablespoonful into hot oil. Deep-fry until golden brown or desired crispiness. Drain on paper towels.

title: mom's ham loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Form in a loaf and bake in a loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mozzarella zucchini special
directions: In 8-inch skillet heat margarine until bubbly and hot, add celery and garlic.
Saute until garlic is lightly browned.
Add zucchini and saute until tender - crisp.
Stir in tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer until most of the liquid has evaporated; 5 - 10 minutes.

title: popovers
directions: Note:
All ingredients should be at room temperature.

title: gumdrop chews
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Blend biscuit mix and brown sugar in a mixing bowl.
Beat eggs, milk, vanilla extract and orange extract until blended.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients and add liquid mixture all at one time.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Carefully scrape around sides and bottom of bowl several times during mixing.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes or until delicately browned.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen chews.

title: peppery corn and tomatoes
directions: Prepare corn as directed on package, using a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until hot.

title: sweet potato casserole with praline topping
directions: Bake potatoes.
Take skins off, cool and mash well.
Add 1/2 cup butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk to sweet potatoes, mixing well.
Pour the mixture into a baking pan or casserole dish.
Bring the cream to a simmer in small saucepan.
Add the brown sugar and stir until dissolves.
Cook the mixture over medium heat until it reaches the soft ball stage on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and beat in the melted butter and chopped pecans.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° until hot and beginning to brown.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together corn, eggs, cream, salt and 1/2 the cracker crumbs.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining crackers on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Serves 18 to 20.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 375°.
Remove pie crust from freezer.
tags: Pet-Ritz deep dish pie crust shell

title: aunt clara's jam cake
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar.
Cream together until light and fluffy.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour, salt and spices. Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mixture.
Add flour mixture to the creamed mixture slowly and beat well after each addition.
Lightly dredge fruit and nuts with extra flour and add to mixture.
Add jam and stir well.
Pour batter into greased and wax-paper lined pans.
Use 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Ice with a caramel icing.

title: nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 1/4 of the tortilla chips on each of 2 ovensafe platters or baking sheets.
In medium bowl, toss cheese, chilies and onion to mix.
Sprinkle 1/4 of the cheese mixture over chips on each platter.
Top with remaining chips and cheese mixture.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve at once.

title: peanutty crunch
directions: Mix cereal and peanuts in large bowl.
Melt almond bark in microwave (small bowl) for 3 or 4 minutes, stirring once or twice. Pour over mix and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. Let stand until hardens.

title: my favorite banana bread
directions: Blend sugar, butter and lemon rind together until light and creamy.
Beat in egg.

Sift together flour, baking powder and soda. Alternately add the sifted ingredients to the sugar mixture with the banana pulp, beating batter after each addition until smooth. Place in greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well with powdered sugar and roll in marble size balls.
Dip in chocolate melted with paraffin in a double boiler.

title: squash casserole
directions: Soak bread in milk and eggs.
Mix other ingredients. Put cereal or crackers on top, crushed.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter over top.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles good.

title: baked fish
directions: Season fillets with seasoned salt and pepper.
In melted butter, place fillets.
Remove fillets from butter and coat in buckwheat flour and place back into melted butter again.
Once fish is covered with butter, remove fish and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend ingredients in a bowl and serve on apple slices. Refrigerate in an airtight container.

title: mix for meat loaf
directions: Fry bacon, onion, celery, green pepper and bay leaves until brown.
Add remaining ingredients and shape meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Shake chicken in plastic bag containing enough flour to coat it heavily.
Mix apricot nectar and onion soup.
Spray a roasting pan with Pam and place floured legs in it.
Pour nectar and soup over the legs and cover.
Cook in 350° oven until chicken is tender.
(You may use whole chicken, cut up, if you like.)

title: baked creamy cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, sugar and crumbs. Press on bottom of pie pan.
Beat cheese until fluffy.
Slowly add Eagle Brand until smooth.
Beat in eggs and lemon juice.
Pour in pan and bake for 50 minutes or until the center is firm.
Top with sour cream.
Bake approximately 8 minutes longer.
Cool and chill. Top with desired fruit topping.
(You may substitute pie crust with ready made frozen graham cracker pie crust.)

title: red apple sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, mix all ingredients and heat until red hots and marshmallows are dissolved.
Add more red hots or marshmallows as desired for color or fluffiness.
Add a small amount of sugar, if needed.
Applesauce can be served warm or cold. Keeps well for a long time in refrigerator.

title: back to basics vegetable soup
directions: Place raw vegetables in food processor. Process until finely chopped. Put vegetables into Dutch oven or 6-cup saucepan.	Add water, garlic, seasonings and tomatoes. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer uncovered until the carrots are tender about 20 minutes. Do not overcook. Serve hot or cold. Yields 6 servings. Serving size is 1 cup or 8 ounces.

title: beef broccoli pie
directions: Brown the meat and onion.
Drain fat.
Stir in flour, salt and garlic.
Add milk and cream cheese.
Cook and stir until mix is smooth and bubbly.
Add moderate amount mixture to egg and return egg to skillet.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Stir in cooked broccoli.
Set aside.

title: pineapple cherry cake
directions: Evenly spread pineapple in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Carefully, spread pie filling on top. Sprinkle with dry cake mix. Dot with butter. Bake in oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Spray pie pan or baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Place sliced apples at the bottom of the dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.
It is good with ice cream.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and spread in baking pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: shrimp and sausage jambalaya
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2 inch slices.
Heat oil in Dutch oven and brown sausage.
Remove.
Add onion, bell pepper, and celery.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened.
Add broth and spices.
Lift tomatoes out of juice (reserving juice), break tomatoes up with a spoon, and add to pan.
Add about half the juice.
Bring to a boil. Add sausage.
Reduce heat and simmer about 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook through (3 to 5 minutes).
Serve over rice.
(Use remainder of tomato juice if more liquid is needed.
Adjust spices to taste.)

title: nancy's lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna; drain.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Brown ground round; drain.
Add jar of spaghetti sauce.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Use half of mixture to cover bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Fill with diced rhubarb.
Cook last 4 ingredients until thick and clear.
Pour evenly over rhubarb. Cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: easy no knead buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and beaten egg. Blend in 1/2 of the flour; mix well.
Stir in oil and rest of flour.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down and make into buns.
Let rise until double in size and bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put all vegetables and water in a large soup kettle and simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Put in jars and cook in hot water bath for 2 hours.

title: butterscotch apple cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt in bowl.
In another bowl, combine butter, brown sugar and egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour mixture alternately with apple juice.
Stir in grated apple, raisins, nuts and 1 1/2 cups butterscotch flavored morsels.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Fry approximately 8 strips of bacon.
Dry and crumble in mixture. Use grease from bacon to bake in cornbread.
Bake at 350°.

title: spicy tomato soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat over medium.
Add more curry if desired.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix all.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tangy cheese spread
directions: Put all ingredients into food processor.
Blend well; process until smooth.
Put cheese spread into a serving container or shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts or parsley.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: cheese bread sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Add yeast to warm water.
Add sugar. Set aside until yeast activates and foams on top.
Add oil.

title: poor man's goose
directions: Cut liver into serving sizes.
Brown both sides in fat. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put liver and drippings into a large casserole.
Add onions and potatoes; sprinkle with more salt and pepper.
Top with bacon slices.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Then uncover and bake 15 minutes longer to crisp bacon.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush up graham crackers (fine).
In a very large bowl mix all the ingredients up after you chop them.
Put in the milk last. Line cracker box with wax paper or you can use a cookie tin. Press mixture in box.

title: low-fat chicken santa fe
directions: In medium bowl, combine tomatoes, salsa, onion, garlic and salt; set aside.
Coat chicken with flour.

Spray a large skillet with Pam; add 1 teaspoon olive oil and heat over medium heat. Saute chicken 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Pour sauce over chicken; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: no bake brownies
directions: In heavy saucepan, add milk, marshmallows, chocolate, sugar and salt.
Bring to full rolling boil over medium heat, stirring continuously.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Continue stirring.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Spread in buttered 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
To cut, use knife dipped in hot water.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix and pour into 9 inch pie crust.
Bake 375° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 45-55 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar to taste.
Add cabbage and stir.
Add peanuts to taste just before serving.

title: auntie karen's spinach casserole
directions: Rinse and drain spinach.
Mix spinach with cheeses, egg whites and flour.
Place mixture into a greased casserole dish.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Remove cover and sprinkle with crushed crackers.
Bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: praline pumpkin pie
directions: Combine the last 3 ingredients and press into bottom of the unbaked pie shell.
Prick sides of shell with fork.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in zucchini.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can bake in small individual baking pan reducing baking time.
Have fun! Makes nice gifts!

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Place apples in greased casserole. Press cheese mixture over and into apples.
Pour 1/2 cup cream or canned milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pea and cheese salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce.
Chill until serving time.
Serve mounded on lettuce leaves.

title: fried cauliflower
directions: Cut cauliflower into small pieces. Roll in meal, salt and pepper.
Fry until done.

title: northwoods chicken
directions: Wash rice 4 to 5 times or soak overnight.
Combine everything but rice, cheese and chicken.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze spinach until dry.
Stir together spinach and remaining ingredients.
Blend and chill.
Serve with cheese flavored crackers.

title: chocklit zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chocolate chips.
Sprinkle chips on top and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured) at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add drink mix and pineapple juice. Add ginger ale just before serving and pour over ice cubes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Add whipped cream or Cool Whip last.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Brown meat with onion, bell pepper and celery. Drain. Cook broccoli as package directs. Drain. Combine meat mixture and cooked broccoli with soup and cream cheese. Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste. Brown for about 10 minutes.
Pour into pie shell. Top with grated cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Let cool about 5 minutes before cutting.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, then add French onion soup, smoked sausage and Stove Top stuffing, and oleo then salt and pepper to taste.
Add all ingredients to water you cook potatoes in about 5 to 6 cups water.
Add water to thin.

title: ronnie's brisket
directions: Put all ingredients in a turkey bag; then put bag in a large roaster pan.
Soak overnight in refrigerator.
Don't punch hole in bag.
Put in a 200° oven not over 210°.
Cook at least 8 hours but for each pound of beef cook an hour.
Cool in bag.
Carefully take meat out of bag.
Cut a hole in corner of bag and drain until reaches grease.
Put gravy over sliced brisket.

title: congress soup
directions: Wash 2 cups of bean mixture (all sold in 1 package at store). Place in large dish.
Cover with water and add 2 tablespoons salt. Let stand overnight and drain.
Add 2 quarts water and ham hocks; simmer slowly 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: jimmy's hominy
directions: Drain hominy and add soup, bell pepper and onion to liquid. Add seasoning of choice and simmer mixture until onion and bell pepper are tender.
Add hominy and cook about 10 minutes until hot.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Butter a big flat casserole.
Place a layer of onions on bottom, then a layer of potatoes, then a layer of carrots.
Salt and pepper.
Mix 1/2 can of water with 1 can of soup.
Pour over potatoes and carrots.
Place slightly browned pork chops on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours covered.
Uncover the last 15 minutes if not brown enough.
The amount depend on you.

title: spanish rice a la boarding house
directions: *Can substitute 4 small or 2 large cans tomato sauce for all.

title: applesauce cake(christmas cake)
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon and allspice.
Mix chopped nuts and raisins and dust.
Cream sugar and butter or oleo.
Add eggs and applesauce mixed with soda.
Mix sugar mixture with flour mixture.
Beat until mixed.
Add nuts and raisins.

title: bloody mary
directions: Mix ingredients in 2-quart container and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with vegetable sticks if you desire.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Brown chops in skillet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl.
Place chops in baking dish.
Pour sauce over chops.
Cover and bake in 350° oven 45 to 60 minutes, depending on thickness.

title: veggie dip
directions: Dip for fresh vegetables.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together in greased pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour or longer, depending on oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain.
Cook Cheez Whiz, mushroom soup, onions, butter and water until cheese melts.
Add rice and cooked broccoli.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour. Add nutmeg and toss well into mix. Turn into pie shell and sprinkle with lemon juice. Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup flour. Rub in the butter and sprinkle the topping evenly over apples. Place pie in large heavy paper bag. Fold over twice and close with paper clips. Place bag on cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 1 hour. Remove pie. Let cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done.
Drain.
Mix everything together. Mix in cut up broccoli.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with extra cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: lemon pie filling
directions: Separate eggs while cold.
Beat yolks with fork.
Set whites aside at room temperature for meringue.
Measure cornstarch, sugar and salt into heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Mix well, using wooden or metal spoon.
Add hot water and stir until smooth; put over high heat and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
When mixture begins to thicken, reduce heat, let bubble for 8 minutes, remove and add some of hot mixture into egg yolks and beat until blended.
Then add hot mixture.
Cook at medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add rind and butter; then add lemon juice in 1/4 teaspoons and stir each time. Let cool.

title: butter tea cakes
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Pinch off small balls.
Pat down with fork on cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown.
Store in a covered cookie jar after cooling. Bake at 350°.

title: bean hot dish
directions: Drain and mix beans together.
Place into baking dish.
Cover beans with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
If using crock-pot, cook for 3 hours.
Dried beans may be used after soaking.

title: jenny cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift flour to make 3 1/2 cups; then sift again with soda and cinnamon, in a separate bowl.
Gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture to make a stiff dough.
Mix in nuts and raisins. Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Watch carefully.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Cream until smooth.
Bananas, pineapple or any fruit of your choice can be added.

title: big mama's pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and syrup.
Add eggs, butter, vanilla and nuts. Mix well and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Then lower temperature to 300° and cook for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, peeled and grated zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to batter and mix until well blended.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lemon bread
directions: Blend all ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Bake in two loaf pans (do not have to grease) at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
For glass pans, reduce to 325°.

title: brown and bake chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in 10-inch baking dish.
Place pieces of chipped beef on top of each breast.
Add the rest under the breasts.
Sprinkle sliced mushrooms and almonds on top.
Mix mushroom soup, sour cream and liquid from mushrooms and pour over chicken.
Cover pan with heavy tin foil and seal tightly.
Place in a 250° oven and cook 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Spread cornbread stuffing over top.
Cover, seal and return to oven. Increase heat to 300°.
Cook 30 minutes more.

title: popcorn ballsroswell, new mexico
directions: Pop a bunch of popcorn and put in a big container.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Thaw broccoli just enough to break apart and place in bowl with other ingredients.
Mix until corn bread is moist.
Put mix in a 9 x 11-inch pan that has been greased or sprayed with Pam. Bake approximately 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco in flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar. Pour over flour mixture all at once.
Blend until moistened. Roll out on floured surface.
Makes 4 single crusts.

title: italian style chili
directions: In large kettle or Dutch oven, brown meat with onion.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients (break up tomatoes).
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with shredded cheese and sour cream, if desired.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: gateau de sirop(syrup cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs. Mix well.
Add milk and syrup; mix until smooth.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook and skin chicken.
Tear into bite size pieces.
Drain vegetables and mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Top with Pillsbury biscuits and bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tuna pie
directions: In a bowl, stir together soup, eggs, tuna and pimento.
Set aside.
Mix biscuit mix and hot water.
Knead dough on floured surface until smooth.
Press dough onto bottom and up sides of a greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on dough. Add tuna mixture. Top with remaining cheese.
Garnish with additional pimento. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center is set.
Cool 10 minutes. Serves 6.

title: aunt ida's cranberry mold
directions: Squeeze orange; save the juice and the rind.
Quarter apple and remove the core and seeds, but not the peel.
Grind half the orange rind with the apple, cranberries and nuts.
Add 1 cup of the hot water to the jello and stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate until mixture reaches the consistency of egg whites.
Blend in fruit and nuts into thickened gelatin.
Return to refrigerator until mixture sets.
This is wonderful for the holidays.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Add oil to other ingredients and blend.
Add poppy seed and blend a few seconds longer.

title: quick corn light bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a loaf pan thoroughly; lightly dust with flour.
Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Stir in shortening and buttermilk.
Let mixture set in pan about 15 minutes, then bake for about 45 minutes.
Cover pan with a tea towel and let cool.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Blend with all dry ingredients.
Mix in nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° until done. Check cake mix directions for specific times.

title: old fashion never fail cupcakes
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put in cupcake pans with paper liners.
Makes 12 or 14 cupcakes.

title: fruit squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a greased and floured 10 x 18-inch pan.
Smooth out.
Make square imprints lightly on dough.
Put pie filling in each square.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put on lower rack.
When it starts to brown, put on top rack and brown top.
Use raisin, pineapple, cherry or apple pie filling.

title: chicken zucchini bake
directions: Arrange zucchini in greased baking dish.
Top with chicken. Mix soup, milk and nutmeg.
Spread over chicken.
Mix Bisquick, cheese and egg until crumbly.
Sprinkle over soup mixture. Sprinkle with parsley.
Drizzle with melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Mix all ingredients in heavy skillet.
Cook until water disappears and nuts have a sugary appearance.
Remove from heat and pour nuts onto a baking sheet.
Separate quickly with 2 forks.

title: italian chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Place in crock-pot. Sprinkle with salad dressing mix.
Cook on low for 5 1/2 hours. Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until onion is tender, stirring frequently.
Pour over chicken.
Cook for 30 minutes longer.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix vegetables, chicken and soup in an ungreased 9 inch pie plate.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: crunchy breakfast
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay 8 slices of bread, American cheese, ham and then 8 more slices of bread.
Beat eggs and milk. Pour over mixture and let stand overnight.
Next morning, sprinkle with corn flakes and 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pecan pie(6 pies)
directions: Combine milk, margarine and chocolate. Place over low heat until chocolate melts, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Combine next 6 ingredients. Stir in chocolate mixture. Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: sausage swirls
directions: Lay rolls in rectangular sheet on waxed paper and press seams closed.
Top each with uncooked sausage.
Spread Dijon mustard over sausage.
Roll jelly roll style so as to create a long narrow roll.
Freeze.
Thaw enough to cut and slice approximately 1/2 inch each.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown in 375° oven.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cook 3 minutes and cool.
Add 1 heaping teaspoonful soda and 2 cups flour, sifted.
Bake in slow oven.

title: two lemon pies
directions: Prebake two pie shells.
Separate eggs, setting whites aside for topping.
In the top of a double boiler, stir together the sugar, salt, flour and water.
When well mixed, beat the egg yolks into the mixture.
Place top of double boiler over boiling water in the bottom of the boiler.
Add the lemon juice.
Keep stirring until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and let cool, stirring occasionally.
Pour into prebaked pie shells.
Add 12 tablespoons sugar to egg whites while beating with
a mixer.
When fairly stiff, put on top of pie filling.
Brown for about 5 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Blend in chicken bouillon granules, salt, sage and pepper.
Add milk and water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cooked chicken, vegetables and parsley.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour into 2 individual casseroles.
Quarter 2 biscuits in each casserole. Place half of the biscuit pieces atop hot filling.
Place casseroles on baking sheet; arrange remaining biscuits on baking sheet alongside casserole.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are browned.
Makes 2 servings.

title: fresh blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in blueberries and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and boiling.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Place in oven to keep hot.

title: dill-icious cucumber dressing
directions: Blend and serve.
A great complement to green, vegetable and chicken salads.

title: oatmeal crispy cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together. Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour, salt and baking soda. Add oats and nuts. Roll in 2 small logs and wrap in wax paper. Chill thoroughly. Slice 1/4-inch thick. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: picnic peas
directions: In a skillet heat oil over medium high.
Saute green pepper, onion and celery.
Add sugar, bay leaf, peas, tomatoes, half of the tomato juice, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove to a bowl and sprinkle with bacon.
Serve hot or room temperature.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pie meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and salt until foamy. Gradually add sugar and beat until stuff, but not dry.
Spread meringue on top of filling, sealing carefully to edge of crust. Bake on baking sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or unti golden brown.

title: mom's peanut brittle
directions: Boil together first 4 ingredients to 250°, then add next 2 ingredients.
Cook.
Stir all the time until reaches 302°.
Remove from heat; add soda and vanilla.
Stir thoroughly, then pour out on well-greased table or large pan.
Stretch thin as desired.

title: pacific lime mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the water, then add the juice from the pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickened, but frothy.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix with a mixer.
Pour into a mold or pan and chill until firm.

title: old-fashioned barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onion, pepper and celery.
Saute until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; remove.
Add to meats and simmer.

title: duck and wild rice
directions: Boil ducks in plenty of water with strip of bacon, pod of hot pepper and minced onion.
Salt to taste.
Duck needs to boil a long time to be tender.
The meat will pull away from breast bone when ready.
Bone duck and cut into bite size pieces.

title: luscious apple rolls
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves; stir in butter.
Set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; cut shortening into flour mixture with
a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to a 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread apples evenly over dough; roll up jellyroll fashion and beginning with long side, cut into 12 (1-inch) slices.
Place slices cut side down in a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour sugar syrup around slices.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
If desired, serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cook and drain ground beef.
Add salsa, olives and diced cheese.
Put in crock-pot or microwave until cheese is melted. Serve hot with Tostitos chips.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand for 24 hours before serving.

title: skillet polenta squares
directions: Bring water and broth to a boil in a saucepan.
Using a wire whisk, gradually stir in 1 cup cornmeal.
Return to a boil. Reduce heat and cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Add whipping cream; cook 20 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in cheese.
tags: shredded Monterey Jack cheese with peppers

title: fresh pear nut cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and oil.
Beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to sugar mixture, one cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, cinnamon, pears and nuts. Spoon batter into well greased 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Powdered sugar glaze if desired. Remove cake from pan when cool and glaze.

title: ham and cheese pinwheels
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth; stir in horseradish and chives.
Spread each meat slice with about 1 tablespoon cream cheese mixture.
Top with cheese slice and spread 1 more tablespoon of cream cheese mixture on cheese.
Roll up; chill.
Before serving, slice each roll into small pieces.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix well. Press into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: dorothy's strudel
directions: Melt 2 sticks margarine.
Set aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan, pour large can of crushed pineapple (plus juice). Next, spread a can of cherry, apple or blackberry pie filling over pineapple.
Then sprinkle a box of yellow cake mix (dry) over this.
Pour melted margarine over the cake mix.
Top with 2 or more cups of chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Delicious served warm!

title: cinnamon nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place raisins in 1/2 cup boiling water. Cool and drain but reserve the water.
Cream sugar, shortening and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture, alternating with reserved water and mixing well.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour loaf pan (or muffin tins) and bake 30 minutes until done.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except water.
Simmer ten minutes.
Add water and cook on medium-high for about 30 minutes.

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Saute garlic, onion and celery until clear.
Add parsley, salt, pepper and marjoram.
Stir in cubes and toss until coated.
Place shrimp in 9 x 9-inch greased pan, sprinkle with lemon juice.
Spread bread mixture lightly over shrimp.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes or until top is brown.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Shield pie crust with foil the last few minutes to prevent overbrowning.

title: fat-free chicken cream gravy
directions: Add flour to skim milk.
Beat or stir until smooth.
Place broth or drippings and onion in saucepan; heat to boiling.
Add flour-milk mixture to broth very slowly, stirring constantly. Season and reduce heat.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: awesome chocolate whoppers(a must for chocolate lovers)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Bake pecans about 8 minutes until lightly brown. Cool and break into large pieces. In a saucepan melt the semi-sweet and unsweetened chocolate and butter over low heat.
Mix and remove from the heat.

title: pecan bit cheese ball(a family favorite)
directions: In
a
small bowl combine cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, onion, sweet pickles and salt; mix well.
(Use hands to get it really mixed.)

title: chicken ole
directions: First mix soups and sour cream together, then add chopped chicken to the mixture, also add the green chilli and the onion. Layer with tortillas first.
Top layer should end with tortillas, then add cheese.
Cook in crock-pot on low 4 to 5 hours.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Mix sugar and flour together and add to crushed pineapple. Stir in beaten eggs.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread cubes which have been combined with melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is a good side dish for ham and other meats.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Put about 1 inch water over potatoes.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup barbecue sauce and 1/2 stick margarine.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir barbecue sauce into water.
Boil potatoes until done (do not overcook, should be firm). Add another 1/2 cup barbecue sauce only fold together.
Do not stir.
Turn burner down so sauce gets onto potatoes.
Water should not be half above potatoes when last sauce is added.
(Goes well with pork, steak or chicken.)

title: pineapple filling
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stirring constantly, bring mixture to a boil and boil for 2 to 3 minutes or until the filling is thick enough to spread. Stir in butter and spread on cake.

title: chocolate kisses
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Add vanilla, sugar and chocolate.
Drop on greased tins.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and Crisco until looks like meal.
Add water and salt. Roll out on floured board for crust.
Only makes one pie crust.

title: incredible hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat milk and butter in small saucepan until butter is melted. Stir in hot cocoa mix until smooth.
Boil gently 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly, until sauce is slightly thickened.
Serve hot over ice cream.
Makes 2/3 cup.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cut butter into flour and sugar mixture.
Add ice water and nuts.
Work up well.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll into powdered sugar while hot.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla together. Add flour and spices and blend well.
In a separate bowl, using a wooden spoon, blend 2 teaspoons vanilla, the soda and the applesauce.
Add applesauce mixture to flour mixture; blend well. The batter will be stiff so stir until well mixed.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix softened margarine and corn bread mixes.
Add egg and milk; stir well.
Add corn and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes until golden brown and mixture is set (but not as done as corn bread).

title: lite garden chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Marinate for 20 minutes in Italian dressing.
Pour into pan and saute until tender.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add mushrooms, zucchini and tomato; cook approximately 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover until cheese is melted.
Serve over rice.
You can substitute your own favorite vegetables.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions. Combine the soup and mayonnaise together.
Layer ingredients in a buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly. Serves 8.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Cream butter and sugar and beat.
Add egg and beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in berries.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with cream topping.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple-marshmallow delight
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in milk on stove in double boiler until all are melted.
Then set aside to cool.
Whip 1 pint cream.
Drain pineapple well and add to cooled marshmallows and milk.
Fold in whipped cream.
A 9 x 13-inch pan or bowl may be used.
Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs.
Place in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, whip remaining 1/2 pint whipping cream for the topping.
May garnish with cherries.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into 2 baked pie crusts.
After they are cool, top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate sauce cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon over this the cake mix and top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: barbecued broiled chicken
directions: Wash chicken and dry on absorbent paper.
Arrange, skin side down, on rack or cookie sheet.
Combine remaining ingredients and heat until butter is melted.
Brush chicken with mixture and put in preheated broiler about 4 inches from heat.
Broil for 50 to 60 minutes under medium heat, turning 3 or 4 times and brushing with barbecue mixture.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and saute onions and garlic.
Add consomme, water, tomatoes (break whole tomatoes in pieces), V-8 and seasonings. Simmer about 30 minutes.
Add rice, spaghetti and vegetables. Simmer 20 minutes.
This makes a very thick soup.
It may be diluted with tomato juice, V-8 or water, if desired.
Makes about a gallon.

title: sausage souffl
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in covered container in refrigerator overnight. Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for about 1 hour. DO NOT PREHEAT OVEN. Put into cold oven. Done when inserted knife comes out clean.

title: delicious pineapple and orange mandarin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and divide into 3 cake pans; bake at 350° until done (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Cool layers before frosting.

title: baked bluefish
directions: Mix mayo, mustard, white and black pepper in bowl.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place bluefish in shallow baking dish.
Squeeze lemon over fish and cover with mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes and serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt the 1 stick margarine and mix with the graham cracker crumbs.
Pack into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Put first 6 ingredients into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. In small bowl, mix eggs, oil and Bisquick.
Pour over zucchini and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peach cobbler #2
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Put 1/2 cup to 1 cup sugar and peaches in another pan; bring to boil.
Spoon peaches over butter.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and milk together; spoon over peaches. Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: salsa
directions: Chop the tomatoes and peppers in chunks.
Cut scallion into large pieces.
Blend all ingredients in blender.
Keeps up to a week in refrigerator.
Serves 6.
Calories 24 (1/2 c.).
Fat 0 gm., 0% fat.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour pie filling into 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake mix, butter and nuts until crumbly.
Pour over pie filling.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour until bubbly.

title: taco salad
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef; pour off fat.
Add onion, green chilies, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Pour cider in coffee percolator. Put spices in basket of percolator. Plug in and let percolate. Makes 2 cups.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except catsup, in blender.
Then add catsup.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let bread cool for 10 minutes, then turn out of pan.
For best results, wrap in foil and let sit for 24 hours.

title: cream cheese pie shells
directions: Combine oleo and cheese, mixing until smooth. Add flour, mixing well. Chill 1 hour. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place each in a well-greased miniature muffin pan, shaping into a shell. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Allow to cool before filling.

title: crustless ham quiche
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter until lightly browned; drain well and set aside.
Combine next 7 ingredients in container of electric blender; process until well blended.
Combine egg mixture, mushrooms, cheese and ham.
Pour into greased 10-inch quiche dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until set. Quiche should be puffed and golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: impossible pie(makes own crust)
directions: Mix all the above ingredients in a blender.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rotel dip
directions: Add cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes to crock-pot or saucepan and let cheese melt.
Brown hamburger meat and drain fat.
Add taco seasoning to hamburger.
Pour this mixture in with cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Keep warm and serve with tortilla chips.

title: quick microwave fudge
directions: Microwave sugar, butter and milk for 11 minutes on High, stirring twice.
Add chocolate chips, marshmallows, nuts and vanilla.
Stir together.
Put in a pan to cool and set.

title: tomatoes and tortellini
directions: Boil tortellini; drain.
Chop tomatoes; place in a large bowl. Chop basil and parsley; crush garlic and add to tomatoes.
Stir in oil, vinegar, salt and pepper; mix.
Add tortellini to mixture; coat well.
Goes great with a loaf of Italian bread.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Drain and mix corn, mushrooms, water chestnuts, bean sprouts, peas and pimento.
Add cauliflower, bell pepper, onion and celery.

title: merle's sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Roll thin crust and cut out cookies.
Bake on lightly greased sheet at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: betty dedoyard's fudge
directions: Boil sugar, salt, milk and butter exactly 4 1/2 minutes.
Put in large bowl the chocolate, chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and walnuts.
Pour hot mixture over chocolate mixture and stir until smooth.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs, add melted margarine, sour cream, whole kernel corn, creamed corn and corn bread mix.
Mix together.
Bake in 2 1/2 quart casserole sprayed with Pam at 350° 40 to 50 minutes.

title: denny's brown bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together well in a large bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add dry yeast.
Mix well.
Gradually add enough white flour to make a stiff dough; knead and let rise.
Punch down; let rise until doubled in bulk in greased loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Stir flour with 1 cup sugar,
cocoa
and
baking
soda. Mix 1 cup water with vanilla, oil and
vinegar.
Add liquid to dry ingredients and mix well with
wooden spoon.
Place midget 2-inch baking cups on baking sheet.
Spoon
batter
into
cups and fill only half full.
In small mixing
bowl,
mix egg with cream cheese and remaining sugar until
well blended.
Stir in mini
chocolate chips.
Place
teaspoon
of
cream
cheese mixture in each cup. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 23 minutes.
Yields 40 to 42 cupcakes.

title: graham cracker brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and press into greased 9x13 pan.
Bake at 325 degrees about 30-45 minutes.
Cut into squares after cooling.

title: down south "yam" cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
In a large bowl, cream sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add mashed yams, beating well.
Lightly spoon flour in measuring cup; level.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
By hand, fold in pecans, raisins and pineapple.
Spread batter into pan evenly.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Invert on plate and cool completely.
Heat frosting until melted, stirring constantly.
Spoon over cake.

title: wisconsin casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; set aside.
Saute celery and onion in oleo. Mix all ingredients together and pour into a large casserole dish. Heat in oven or microwave.

title: wild rice chicken summer salad
directions: Toss rice, pineapple, celery, grapes, nuts and chicken together.

title: men love it chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, allow to cool; save broth.
Cook rice according to direction on package.
When cool, pulled chicken into bite size pieces.
In a large bowl, combine sour cream, cream of chicken soup and chicken broth; season with salt, pepper and sage to taste.
Mix well. Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
In a zip lock bag, crush crackers into crumbs; add melted butter.
Mix. Sprinkle to cover casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly hot and topping is golden brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans as package directs, but cook just 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix with rest of ingredients, except onion rings.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle top with onion rings.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: relish dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender and mix well.

title: cheddar parmesan potatoes
directions: In saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk and cook; stir until mixture thickens. Put aside and add salt, Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add potatoes; stir until mixed.
Place in 2-quart dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer sauerkraut in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle garlic salt and onion over it.
Top with sour cream; crumble corned beef over this, then cheese.
Top with bread cubes and drizzle melted oleo over bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: curried pasta and chickpea salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Cool under water and drain well.
Chop celery and onions fine.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Serve.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Blend all and pour into pie shell. Bake 40 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Sprinkle chicken lightly with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place chicken breasts in crock-pot.
Mix the white wine, soup and mushrooms until well blended; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle again with paprika.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours or on high 3 to 4 hours. Thirty minutes before serving, remove chicken breasts.
Mix flour and sour cream; add to mixture in crock-pot.
Return chicken to mixture; cook for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: mayhaw creme pie
directions: Combine part of mayhaw with gelatin.
Warm slowly until gelatin dissolves.
Combine with remaining mayhaw.
In mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until soft.
Add sugar.
Beat until well mixed. Add mayhaw; mix in with cream cheese mixture.
When thoroughly mixed, add whipped topping.
Fold in until well mixed.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Chill until firm.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, water, oil and eggs.
Drain and mix strawberries in batter.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Combine sugar and flour or cornstarch.
Add water slowly and mix.
Add butter.
Cook until thickens.
Crumb some graham crackers in bottom of dish.
Slice a layer of bananas on crackers. Put in part of filling.
Repeat layers until filling is used. Sprinkle ground peanuts on top.

title: sherry wine cake
directions: Grease well and lightly flour large Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, mix together nuts, sugar and cinnamon; set aside.

title: sugar and spice pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Pick over pecans for any shell matter. In a large bowl, combine egg white and water, beating with a fork until just frothy.
Combine salt, spices and sugar.
Add pecans to egg white mixture, turning with
a fork to coat all nuts well. Add sugar mixture, again mixing thoroughly.
Pour onto buttered 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan and bake one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool before storing in an airtight container at room temperature.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add cream cheese, egg, Ricotta, basil and pepper.
Set aside. Mix mushroom soup, wine, scallops, shrimp, crab and Parmesan cheese. Layer 3 noodles in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread seafood mixture on top of noodles.
Layer 3 more noodles.
Spread cheese mixture on top.
Layer remaining noodles.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and decorate with a few shrimp.
Cover and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: grandma josie's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix sugars, butter, shortening and egg until creamy.
Add vanilla and stir.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Stir well; add chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers with rolling pin.
Cream sugar and oleo. Add vanilla wafer crumbs, nuts and orange juice.
Blend well and roll in small balls, then roll balls in coconut and let set.

title: chicken corn noodle soup(serves 6)
directions: Boil chicken and onion in water with corn.
When chicken is done, add broth and noodles.
When noodles are done, add parsley flakes and serve.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Beat butter with sugar until mixture is light and fluffy. Beat in vanilla.
Blend salt with flour and stir into beaten mixture, mixing well.
Fold in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Press into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes.
While warm, cut in 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Cool in pan on rack.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: egg custard
directions: Scald the milk; let cool. Blend eggs, sugar and salt.
Slowly stir in slightly cooled milk. Add vanilla. Bake in a 325° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Place custard cups in pan of water to cook.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water, then add beet juice.
Cool until syrupy.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Turn into a ring mold and chill.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Shell and devein shrimp; put aside.
Cook chopped celery, onions, garlic and bell pepper until wilted.
Add roux.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Add remainder of seasonings except parsley.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and let simmer at least 1 hour.
Add shrimp and crabmeat if desired and cook for 15 minutes. Add chopped parsley just before serving.
Serve over hot fluffy rice.
For more highly seasoned sauce, add a little Tabasco. Serves 8.

title: gazpacho(a fresh vegetable soup)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium-size stainless steel or glass bowl.
Cover.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Stir occasionally. Serve cold in a cup.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mother's old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy. Combine flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and allspice. Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms; marinate in dressing overnight.

title: danish sandwich
directions: Cream together butter, powdered sugar, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Form into small balls.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Dust with powdered sugar when cool.

title: soft molasses drops
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, molasses and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Mix thoroughly. Place casserole in pan filled with hot water, 1 inch deep.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: peach-zucchini jam
directions: Peel and shred zucchini.
Combine with lemon juice in a saucepan.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in pineapple and sugar. Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Cook for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal with 2-piece lids.
Process in a boiling water bath for 5 minutes. Yield:
about 7 cups.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Mix together oil, vinegar, catsup, bay leaves, Worcestershire Sauce, salt and mustard.
Pour over shrimp and onions; let marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: zesty beef dip
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, crumble beef.
Add onion and garlic. Over medium-high heat, cook and stir for 5 minutes or until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, catsup, oregano, sugar, pepper and salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spray baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.	Pour dry rice into bottom of dish.
Arrange salted and peppered chicken pieces over rice; sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Mix mushroom soup, chicken soup and chicken broth together and pour over casserole. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Mix in wafers.
Add milk, nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Mix together.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: druken chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish and top with slices of cheese.
Combine soup and wine, spoon over chicken.
Mix stuffing with melted butter and sprinkle on chicken. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Saute onion in oleo (optional).
Add Cheddar cheese soup and milk to macaroni.
Mix and serve.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: While rice is cooking, pound steak and sprinkle with paprika. Let stand while preparing other ingredients.

title: tomato pilaf
directions: Use tomatoes held at room temperature until fully ripe.
Core and chop tomatoes (about 4 cups); set aside.
In a large saucepan, beat oil until hot.
Add garlic; cook until golden, about 1 minute.
Add reserved tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook, uncovered, until tomatoes are slightly softened, about 4 minutes. Add broth; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and sugar.
Simmer, covered, until rice is tender, 15 to 18 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Reheat with additional beef broth, if needed.

title: holiday candy wreaths
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly, until marshmallows melt and mixture is syrupy.
Remove from heat.
Stir in food coloring.
Add cornflakes and stir until coated.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Roll out pie shell. Mix rhubarb, strawberries, sugar, minute tapioca, lemon juice, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt together and place in pie shell. Top pie with crust, cut steam vents. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into small balls and cover with cinnamon.

title: puppy chow
directions: Use brown grocery bag.
Pour cereal in bag.
Take peanut butter, margarine and chocolate chips, melt and pour over cereal, then pour powdered sugar over cereal.
Close bag and shake real well.
Good snack.

title: lollipop sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter flavor Crisco, sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl at medium speed until well blended.
Beat egg into mixture. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture. Cover and refrigerate for several hours, or overnight.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls and push sticks into center of dough.
Place dough, with stick parallel, 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten to 1/2 inch with large, smooth, greased and floured spatula.
Decorate as desired with red hots, coconut, nuts or colored sugar, etc.
Press decoration into dough. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet.

title: crock-pot beef roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast.
Spread on about 1 tablespoon of A.1. steak sauce.
Place roast in broiler pan under broiler for about 10 minutes to brown and remove excess fat.
Put vegetables in bottom of crock-pot.
After browning, place roast on top of vegetables.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 cup water.
Cover; cook on low 10 to 12 hours (high 5 to 6).

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray pizza pan with Pam; press sugar cookie dough to edges of pan.
Bake as directed on package; cool.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add sugar and milk.
Spread on cookie; arrange fruit on pizza.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Cool.
Serve with dollop of Cool Whip.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Put pie crust in pie plate.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef; drain well.
Add bread crumbs, tomato sauce and oregano.
Mix well.
Add onions and/or green pepper, if desired. Fill pie crust with mixture.
Top with 2 beaten eggs.
Sprinkle 1 cup Cheddar or Swiss cheese over pie.
Bake for 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all together well, beating with mixer.
Pour into a greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes at 300°.

title: robbie's pinch cake
directions: Pinch 1 can biscuits at a time and roll in sugar and cinnamon. Place in tube pan.
Melt butter and pour over top of all mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick pineapple dessert
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl; mix well. Pour into a greased 8 x 10-inch pan and sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Top with whipped cream.

title: beans and franks
directions: Pour pork and beans in 1-quart casserole. Add onion soup mix, brown sugar, mustard, ketchup and vinegar.
Mix well.
Place bacon strips across top of beans and bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 375°.
Cut hot dogs in half and stand around edge of casserole. Return to oven and bake 15 minutes longer. Serves 4.

title: sheep herder's bread and dip
directions: Mix all, except the bread.
Cut off top of bread and scoop out inside.
Tear into chunks.
Pour mixture into the bread.
Stuff as much bread as possible into dip and put on bread lid.

title: rice-a-roni jambalaya
directions: Brown rice portion of package in margarine. Add water and seasoning packet from rice package.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until water is gone.
Also good using 2 cups chicken pieces (bite size), 1/2 cup chopped walnuts instead of shrimp.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and spread in uncooked pie shell.

title: dump it cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the order listed. Layer it, do not mix.
Pat down the dry yellow cake mix after putting into pan.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: party chicken
directions: Place 1/2 chicken breast on 3 slices dried beef.
Wrap each one with one slice bacon.
Place in greased or buttered casserole dish (single layer).
Mix soup and sour cream and spread over chicken.
Bake 3 1/4 hours at 275°.

title: frog eye salad(very low-fat)
directions: Drain fruit and save juice.
Cook macaroni 10 minutes in water; drain.
Rinse and cool.
Bring to a boil 3/4 cup juice, mixed with sugar and salt.
Stir in cornstarch mixture; stir until thick.
Cool.
Mix into fruit and macaroni.
Add marshmallows. Fold in sour cream; let stand 12 to 24 hours for best flavor.

title: mocha spice cake
directions: Stir spice and coffee into Master Cake Mix. Add 1/2 cup milk and beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs, vanilla and remaining milk; beat 2 minutes, scraping bowl and beaters as needed.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: Put cream cheese in microwave for 2 minutes.
Then add canned chili and green chilies.
Heat again for 3 minutes; add cheese on top.
Dip with chips.

title: lemon frosted angel cake(serves 12 plus)
directions: Cut cake horizontally into 4 layers using a serrated knife. In medium bowl combine pie filling and yogurt; blend well.
Spread 1/3 of filling (about 1 cup) between each cake layer.
Frost top and sides with whipped topping.
Garnish with lemon slices. Store in refrigerator.

title: sandbakkelse
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add and cream egg, flour and cardamom.
Chill dough 3 hours or overnight.

title: bean dip and nachos
directions: Grate Monterey Jack cheese and Cheddar cheese; mix.
Pack refried beans in a greased pie plate.
Spread cheese mixture over beans.
Spread green peppers and jalapeno peppers on top; bake until the cheese melts.
Serve with nacho or tortilla chips for dipping.

title: southern crackling cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, soda, and
salt. Mix well. Stir in beaten eggs and milk. Heat bacon drippings
pan until hot. Add drippings and cracklings to batter. Mix well. Pour into hot pan. Bake at 450° for 25 minutes until bread is golden. Cut in squares. Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Have ready a 9-inch crust. Turn on oven and set at 375° (high moderate).

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix chocolate chips, salt and powdered sugar until firm.
Melt chocolate chips.
Grease muffin tin.
Pour chocolate into cups, filling halfway.
Draw chocolate up to edges until all sides are coated.
Spoon peanut butter in middle.
Pour chocolate over top and spread evenly to edges.

title: gramma kopp's chili sauce
directions: Chop and clean off seeds on all vegetables and put into heavy pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well over medium heat. Bring to a boil, then simmer until thick.
Watch carefully because it will be over an hour.
Happy cooking.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Lemon Sauce; marinate chicken breasts 4 hours or longer in the refrigerator. Use enough vegetable oil to cover bottom of skillet. Fry chicken, skin side down, over medium heat. Fry until crisp and golden brown. Turn chicken and fry other side. Serve with Lemon Sauce.

title: klotchke
directions: Mix cream cheese and oleo.
Add flour and mix.
Add flour to mix like pie dough.
Roll out; cut into 2 inch squares.
Add dab of apricot jam.
Fold opposite corners.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: my favorite ham
directions: Rub ham until coated with brown sugar.
Stick in 15 to 20 whole cloves.
Place 4 slices of pineapple on ham and wrap in tinfoil. Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and canning salt.
Cover with ice water and let stand 3 hours.
Mix vinegar, sugar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed.
Cook until hot.
Drain cucumbers and add to brine.
Boil up, pack and seal.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Mix
together
and
roll
into	balls; butter bottom of glass and
dip
into granulated sugar and mash each ball.
Dip the glass for each cookie.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes about 9 dozen.

title: cantaloupe soup
directions: Combine apple juice, orange juice, wine and tapioca in a medium saucepan; let stand 5 minutes.
Bring mixture to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Cool completely; stir in red pepper.
Finely chop one cantaloupe and add to soup.
Refrigerate until serving.
To serve, ladle into bowls; top with whipped cream and garnish with mint leaves.
Serves 6.

title: hurry up donuts
directions: Fill skillet (preferably iron) with 1 to 2 inches of oil or shortening.
Heat on high, then turn down to medium-high.
Pull biscuits apart and make large hole in center.
Drop gently into hot oil and brown, then turn over to brown on other side.
Drain on paper towel, then drop in bowl with sugar.
Cover bowl; shake and serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: Boil spiral noodles until done.
Drain noodles and rinse with cold water.
In large bowl, mix Catalina dressing, 3/4 of the bottle of Salad Supreme or to your taste and 2 large cucumbers, chopped in cubes.
Mix well and add the noodles.
Add more dressing if needed.
Refrigerate.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs well and add to mixture.
Mash bananas until smooth; add lemon juice and blend with mixture.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt; quickly add to the banana mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: 20 minute cupcakes
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and powder.
Add water, vinegar, vanilla and oil.
Stir mixture fast.
Put in cupcake liners or cupcake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 16.

title: leslie's sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes.
In a skillet on medium heat, add water, sweet potatoes, cinnamon, allspice and vanilla.
Cook covered for 20 minutes.
Add sugar, butter and pineapple juice. Cook 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter (margarine) in a saucepan. Add sugar.
Stir in eggs; add flour, salt, vanilla and baking powder.
Add nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes.

title: 3 bean enchiladas
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans and bring to a boil; cover and cook 2 minutes. Remove from heat; let stand one hour.
Drain beans; return to Dutch oven.
Add 6 cups water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until beans are tender. Drain, reserving 1/4 cup liquid (add water, if necessary, to make 1/4 cup).
Place beans in container of an electric blender or food processor; add reserved 1/4 cup liquid, onion and next 5 ingredients.
Process 5 seconds or until mixture is chunky.
Brush tortillas with water.
Divide bean mixture among tortillas.
Roll up; place seam side down in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Pour enchilada sauce over tortillas.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Yield:

12 servings (177 calories per enchilada), each containing 9.8 grams protein, 2.1 grams fat, 31.5 grams carbohydrate, 4.5 grams fiber, 2 milligrams cholesterol, 233 milligrams sodium and 136 milligrams calcium.

title: chili
directions: Dice bacon and cook until crisp in pan.
In drippings brown onion and mushrooms.
Set aside.
Brown beef.
Pour off fat and add all remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour uncovered.
Freezes well.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients; shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on nonstick cookie sheet; bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese crusted cauliflower
directions: Steam cauliflower until tender.
Place in baking dish.
Mix mayonnaise and Dijon mustard to your taste.
Spread on top of cauliflower.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Broil until melted and crisp.

title: holiday pound cake
directions: Cream butter until soft and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually beating thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Add
eggs,
one
at
a time, beating well after each egg
is
added.
Sprinkle
cherries and nuts with 1/4 cup of the flour.
Sift remaining flour with salt and fold 1/2 cup at a time into the creamed mixture mixing only until smooth.
Fold in cherries and nuts with the last addition of flour. Bake in greased and
floured
10-inch
tube pan or in two loaf pans in a slow oven (300°
to
325°) for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions; drain.
In a skillet, melt butter; add beef and onion and brown.
Add 1 can pizza sauce, tomato paste, garlic salt and oregano; simmer 10 to 15 minutes. In a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan, layer 1/3 noodles, 1/3 meat and 1/3 cheese; repeat.
Spread with can of pizza sauce and top with remaining cheeses.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar, beating well.
Add flour and almond flavoring, mixing well.
Add cut up fruit and nuts; mix well. Makes 2 cakes in tube pans.
Cook at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Put water in cookie sheet on rack under cakes to keep from being so dry.
Put brown paper in bottom of pans.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish. Combine flour, sugar, milk and peaches. Pour into dish. Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Heat water; add tea, cider, lemon juice, sugar and spices. Put into crock-pot and serve warm.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: little cheesecakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, eggs and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed with hand mixer for 5 minutes.
Line small (1/2-inch in diameter) cupcake pans with paper liners.
Put one vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner with flat side down.
Put 1 tablespoon cheesecake mixture into each cup.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until the cracks appear on top of each cake.
Remove from oven and let cool.
They will appear to fall.
Drop 1 teaspoon of your choice of pie filling onto top of each cheesecake.

title: mayonnaise drop biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Take flour, mayonnaise and sweet milk and mix together.
Bake in well-greased muffin tins for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain. Add chili powder, tomatoes, Texas Pete and oregano. Add 1/2 cup water and simmer. Add pintos and kidney beans.

title: seafood delight
directions: Saute onion, peppers and mushrooms in butter 5 minutes. Reserve. Stir flour into pan. Gradually stir in cream until smooth and thick.

Stir in vegetables and season. Add seafood. Cook 2 minutes. Beat egg yolk and stir hot sauce into egg yolk, a few tablespoons at a time. Add to white sauce. Remove from heat and add sherry. Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: nana morgan's peanut butter cookies(double batch)
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter and sugar; add eggs. Sift flour and soda.
Add to first mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Form into balls the size of a walnut; flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients and add to browned hamburger and onions.
Mixture will be watery until it cooks down.
Simmer for about 40 minutes, stirring to prevent sticking.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: Heat cornstarch and apple juice until boils and thickens. Mixture will be thick.
Add spices and apples.
Fold together well.

title: southern snow storm
directions: In an 8 ounce coffee glass add Southern Comfort, peppermint Schnapps and fill with hot cocoa.
Add whipped cream.

title: veggie stack up
directions: In 2 1/2-quart clear glass bowl, layer lettuce, peppers, corn, zucchini, tomatoes and celery.
Mix 1 cup Miracle Whip and 1 cup salad dressing and spread over top of celery, sealing to edges of bowl.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon on top just before serving.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Put in a large casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with sour cream.
Beat until smooth. Add flavoring; mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour or until done.
Can be sprinkled with powdered sugar or glazed.

title: carolyn's potato salad
directions: Wash and cube potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Chop onions and add all other ingredients together.
Drain potatoes, then add to mixture.
May be served hot or cold.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 325° for 4 1/4 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Stir all ingredients together, except bacon.
Put in a baking dish.
Lay bacon on top of beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lobster bisque elegante
directions: Bring enough water to a boil to cover lobster tails; add 1 tsp. salt to each 1 qt. of water. Drop frozen lobster trails into water and boil 11 minutes (or 3 minutes plus the weight of the largest lobster tail). Remove meat from the lobster shells and dice. Set aside. Crush shells and put in a saucepan. Add the 3 c. water, seasoned stock base, onion flakes, coriander seed, bay leaf, vegetable flakes and peppercorns. Simmer 30 minutes;

and strain. Melt butter; stir in flour, Bon Appetit and salt. Cook until bubbly. Remove from heat and add milk. Simmer over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Stir in lobster stock, lobster meat and cream. DO NOT allow it to boil. Serve piping hot.

title: garlicky green rice
